(638, 1, '2012-05-14 17:14:31', '2012-05-14 11:44:31', '', 'color+tab', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', 'colortab', '', '', '2012-05-14 17:14:31', '2012-05-14 11:44:31', '', 0, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/answers/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2012/05/color+tab.png', 0, 'attachment', 'image/png', 0),
(668, 1, '2012-06-01 16:30:18', '2012-06-01 11:00:18', 'This may be due to incorrect File Permissions.\n\nYou need to change the file permissions of <strong>"lang"</strong> folder inside all the <strong>modules</strong>, <strong>plugins</strong> and <strong>extensions</strong> folders.\n\nIf you are using <strong>Linux System</strong>, you need to <strong>CHMOD</strong> the folder to <strong>777 (read/write/execute)</strong>.\n\nIf you are using <strong>Windows System</strong>, right click on the <strong>folder/file</strong> -&gt; <strong>Properties</strong> -&gt; <strong>Security</strong>. To change the file permissions, click on <strong>Edit</strong> -&gt; <strong>Allow full control</strong>.</ul>\n\n\n', 'I am unable to create/edit a new language through CometChat Administration Panel.', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'i-am-unable-to-createedit-a-new-language-through-cometchat-administration-panel', '', '', '2012-06-01 16:30:18', '2012-06-01 11:00:18', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=668', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(678, 1, '2012-05-16 16:26:29', '2012-05-16 10:56:29', '', 'TCC', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', 'tcc', '', '', '2012-05-16 16:26:29', '2012-05-16 10:56:29', '', 0, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/answers/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2012/05/TCC.png', 0, 'attachment', 'image/png', 0),
(700, 1, '2012-06-01 15:58:19', '2012-06-01 10:28:19', 'If you are facing this issue then your base URL is incorrect.\n\nWhen the base URL is incorrect, the images will not appear and CometChat will fail to function.\n\nThe <strong>BASE_URL</strong> is usually <strong>/cometchat/</strong> when the CometChat folder is uploaded to the root.\n\nTo modify the Base URL:\n\nLog into <strong>Administration Panel</strong> =&gt; <strong>Settings</strong> tab =&gt; <strong>Change Base URL</strong> =&gt; Change the path =&gt; <strong>Update Settings</strong>\n\nFor example,\n\n1) If CometChat is accessible at the URL: <strong>http://www.demosite.com/dev/cometchat</strong>, then BASE_URL should be <strong>"/dev/cometchat/"</strong> (no quotes).\n\n2) If CometChat is accessible at the URL : <strong>http://www.demosite.com/dev/forum/cometchat</strong>, then BASE_URL should be <strong>"/dev/forum/cometchat/"</strong> (no quotes).\n\n3) If CometChat is installed in <strong>cross-domain environment</strong> and is accessible at the URL <strong>http://chat.demosite.com</strong>, then BASE_URL should be <strong>"http://chat.demosite.com/"</strong> (no quotes).', 'Who''s Online list appears empty on my chat bar. Please help.', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'whos-online-list-appears-empty-on-my-chat-bar-please-help', '', '', '2012-06-01 15:58:19', '2012-06-01 10:28:19', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=700', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(708, 1, '2012-06-01 16:32:45', '2012-06-01 11:02:45', 'If the Tray icons are not displayed on your CometChat bar then either of the following could be the issue:\n\n<strong>1. Your Base URL is incorrect</strong>\n\nIf your Base URL is incorrect, please refer to <a href="/answers/whos-online-list-appears-empty-on-my-chat-bar-please-help/">this article</a>.\n\n<strong>2. Images have not been uploaded correctly</strong>\n\nIf you have uploaded the images in <strong>ASCII mode</strong>, then your images will appear as corrupted. Make sure your images are uploaded in <strong>BINARY mode</strong> only.', 'Tray icons are not displayed on my CometChat bar. How can I fix this?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'tray-icons-are-not-displayed-on-my-cometchat-bar-how-can-i-fix-this', '', '', '2012-06-01 16:32:45', '2012-06-01 11:02:45', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=708', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(726, 1, '2012-05-18 18:32:34', '2012-05-18 13:02:34', 'If you get ''Unable to connect to database'' error, refer to the solutions listed below:\n\n<strong>1. Re-download CometChat</strong>\n\nThe most common cause of this issue is an <strong>incorrectly downloaded integration file</strong>. If you are integrating CometChat with WordPress and you select BuddyPress from the drop-down menu before download, the installation will not work correctly.\n\n<strong>2. Incorrect Folder</strong>\n\nThe CometChat folder must be uploaded to the <strong>correct directory</strong>. Please make sure you upload it to the software <strong>root folder</strong>.\n\n<strong>3. Custom Site</strong>\n\nIf you are integrating CometChat with a <strong>custom site</strong>, you will have to manually edit <strong>integration.php</strong> and add the database details. Do not make this modification if you are using any ready-to-use integration like WordPress, vBulletin etc.', 'I get ''Unable to connect to database'' error when I try to add CometChat on my site.', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'i-get-unable-to-connect-to-database-error-when-i-try-to-add-cometchat-on-my-site', '', '', '2012-05-18 18:32:34', '2012-05-18 13:02:34', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=726', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(728, 1, '2012-06-01 16:21:37', '2012-06-01 10:51:37', 'If you are unable to find the &lt;HEAD&gt; tag in your site template, you will have to perform the following steps:\n\nYou need to manually edit <strong>libraries/joomla/document/html/renderer/head.php</strong>. Please backup this file before proceeding.\n\nFind the following comment on line 87:\n\n<pre>// Generate link declarations</pre>\n\nAdd the following code just before the comment:\n\n<pre><code>$strHtml .= ''&lt;link type="text/css" rel="stylesheet" media="all" href="/cometchat/cometchatcss.php" charset="utf-8" /&gt;&lt;script type="text/javascript" src="/cometchat/cometchatjs.php" charset="utf-8"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;'';\n</code></pre>\n\nSo the new code will look like:\n\n<pre><code>$strHtml .= ''&lt;link type="text/css" rel="stylesheet" media="all" href="/cometchat/cometchatcss.php" charset="utf-8" /&gt;&lt;script type="text/javascript" src="/cometchat/cometchatjs.php" charset="utf-8"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;'';\n\n// Generate link declarations\n</code></pre>\n\n<blockquote>$strHtml variable name may be different (e.g. $buffer) in different Joomla installations.</blockquote>\n\nSave your file and then you can continue with the rest of the installation.', 'I am unable to find HTML code in my Joomla site template.', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'i-am-unable-to-find-html-code-in-my-joomla-site-template', '', '', '2012-06-01 16:21:37', '2012-06-01 10:51:37', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=728', 0, 'post', '', 0);
