(1305, 1, '2012-08-23 14:27:26', '2012-08-23 08:57:26', 'This issue will only happen if you are using CometService on the sender''s side. On the receiver''s side, the smiley image will always be seen.\n', 'When I write a text smiley in a chat window, it is rendered only when I close and reopen the window.', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'when-i-write-a-text-smiley-in-a-chat-window-it-is-rendered-only-when-i-close-and-reopen-the-window', '', '', '2012-08-23 14:27:26', '2012-08-23 08:57:26', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=1305', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1344, 1, '2012-08-23 14:19:57', '2012-08-23 08:49:57', 'To replace "Who''s Online" on the chat bar:\n\nGo to <strong>CometChat Administration Panel</strong> -&gt; click on <strong>language</strong> tab -&gt; <strong>"Edit Language"</strong> option -&gt; <strong>Core</strong> -&gt; Change <strong>"Who''s Online"</strong> to <strong>"Friend''s Online"</strong> -&gt; Click on <strong>"Update Language"</strong>.\n\nAlternatively, you can manually edit <strong>/cometchat/lang/en.php</strong> file and delete all files in <strong>/cometchat/cache</strong> directory.\n\nCometChat v4.4.0 has an inbuilt caching mechanism to reduce the the load/response time of CometChat on your site.\n\n<blockquote>Note: If you make changes through the CometChat Administration Panel, the cache gets cleared automatically. You need to clear the cache manually only if you have edited /cometchat/lang/en.php file.</blockquote>\n', 'I want to replace "Who''s Online" on the chat bar with "Friend''s Online". How can I do that?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'i-want-to-replace-whos-online-on-the-chat-bar-with-friends-online-how-can-i-do-that', '', '', '2012-08-23 14:19:57', '2012-08-23 08:49:57', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=1344', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1406, 1, '2012-08-23 14:30:43', '2012-08-23 09:00:43', 'CometChat has a feature that displays a <strong>pencil-image</strong> next to the user''s name at the top of the chat window when the user is typing.\n\nHowever, note that this is an experimental feature and may NOT work at all. We provide no support for this feature.\n\nTo enable this feature, set <strong>''DISABLE_ISTYPING''</strong> to <strong>0</strong> in the <strong>/cometchat/config.php</strong> file i.e. \n<strong>define(''DISABLE_ISTYPING'',''0'')</strong>;	', 'How will I know that the other user is typing during an one-on-one conversation?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'how-will-i-know-that-the-other-user-is-typing-during-one-on-one-conversation', '', '', '2012-08-23 14:30:43', '2012-08-23 09:00:43', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=1406', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1414, 1, '2012-08-23 14:26:21', '2012-08-23 08:56:21', 'CometChat loses its layout on your website because of incorrect loading of the CSS file. \n\nIf the CSS is not loading, follow the set of procedures listed below:\n\n	<li>\n\n<ol>\n\nLoad <strong>cometchat/css.php</strong> in the browser and save the contents into <strong>cometchat/cometchat.css file</strong>.\n\n</ol>\n\n </li>\n	<li>\n<ol>\n\nEdit the CometChat HTML code to point to the <strong>cometchat/cometchat.css</strong> file instead of the <strong>cometchat/css.php</strong>\n\n</ol>\n\n\n</li>\n\n	<li>\n\n<ol>\n\n\nMake sure that the CometChat HTML code is added immediately after the <strong> head tag </strong>of your site.\n\n</ol>\n\n</li>\n\n', 'CometChat looses its layout on my website and sometimes works fine after I reload the page. What could be the issue?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'cometchat-looses-its-layout-on-my-website-and-sometimes-works-fine-after-i-reload-the-page-what-could-be-the-issue', '', '', '2012-08-23 14:26:21', '2012-08-23 08:56:21', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=1414', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1501, 1, '2012-08-23 14:26:52', '2012-08-23 08:56:52', 'To embed chatroom on your site page:\n\n1. Login into <strong>CometChat Administration Panel</strong> -&gt; <strong>modules</strong> -&gt; Click on the <strong>Generate Embed Code</strong> button next to the Chatrooms module.\n\n2. A window pops out with the <strong>iframe HTML code</strong> as shown in the image below.\n\n<img src="http://v6.cometchat.com/answers/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2012/06/embedCR.png" alt="embedCR" />\n \n3. Copy the code and add to your site HTML code.', 'How do I add a chatroom to my site page?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'how-do-i-add-chatroom-to-my-site-page', '', '', '2012-08-23 14:26:52', '2012-08-23 08:56:52', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=1501', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1507, 1, '2012-06-11 14:27:52', '2012-06-11 08:57:52', '', 'embedCR', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', 'embedcr', '', '', '2012-06-11 14:27:52', '2012-06-11 08:57:52', '', 0, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/answers/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2012/06/embedCR.png', 0, 'attachment', 'image/png', 0),
(1519, 1, '2012-08-23 14:27:56', '2012-08-23 08:57:56', 'If you are facing this issue, then you need to change the permission of <strong>/cometchat/config.php</strong> file.\n\nChange the file permission to <strong>777 (read/write/execute)</strong> so that all the changes made through the CometChat Administration Panel are reflected on your site.', 'The changes I make in the CometChat Administration Panel are not reflected on my site. What is the issue?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'the-changes-that-i-make-in-the-cometchat-administration-panel-are-not-reflected-on-my-site-what-is-the-issue', '', '', '2012-08-23 14:27:56', '2012-08-23 08:57:56', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=1519', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1529, 1, '2012-08-23 14:32:37', '2012-08-23 09:02:37', 'To reduce load on your Server:\r\n\r\n1. Make sure all your tables are <strong>InnoDB</strong> (it supports row level locking instead of table locking).\r\n \r\n2. Run www.yoursite.com/<br class="visible-phone">cometchat/cron.php every 3 hours to clear your CometChat table entries.\r\n \r\n3. You can avoid <strong>execution of MySQL queries</strong> against your database and improve the performance of the chat system by subscribing to our <strong><a href="http://www.cometchat.com/cometservice">CometService</a></strong> which offloads 95% of the work to our servers.\r\n\r\nWe also provide <a href="http://www.cometchat.com/cometservice/third-party-alternatives">alternative transports</a>- self-hosted APE server, PubNub, PusherApp and BeaconPush which can be used instead of CometService.', 'After installing CometChat, the load on our server is high. What can I do to reduce this load?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'after-installing-cometchat-the-load-on-our-server-is-high-what-can-i-do-to-reduce-this-load', '', '', '2013-09-26 10:24:02', '2013-09-26 10:24:02', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=1529', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1616, 1, '2012-08-23 14:35:21', '2012-08-23 09:05:21', 'To display time in your chat conversation, find the code given below in <strong>themes/[THEME-NAME]/css/cometchat.css</strong>\r\n\r\n<pre><code>.cometchat_ts {\r\n        color: #ccc;\r\n        cursor: default;\r\n        <strong>display: none;</strong>\r\n        font-size: 10px;\r\n        padding-left: 5px;\r\n        padding-top: 2px;\r\n        text-align: left;\r\n}</code></pre>\r\n\r\nReplace it with the following code:\r\n\r\n<pre><code>.cometchat_ts {\r\n        color: #ccc;\r\n        cursor: default;\r\n        <strong>display: inline;</strong>\r\n        font-size: 10px;\r\n        padding-left: 5px;\r\n        padding-top: 2px;\r\n        text-align: left;\r\n}</code></pre>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>Note: CometChat 4.4+ has a caching mechanism and so you need to clear the content of <strong>/cometchat/cache directory</strong> when you manually make any changes to CometChat files.</blockquote>\r\n', 'I want to permanently display chat time in the chat conversation. How can I do that?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'i-want-to-permanently-display-chat-time-in-the-chat-conversation-how-can-i-do-that', '', '', '2013-09-26 10:08:39', '2013-09-26 10:08:39', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=1616', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1628, 1, '2012-08-23 14:34:23', '2012-08-23 09:04:23', 'If you are not using CometService, you cannot completely disable logs. This is because your mySQL table is used to transport data from the sender to the receiver. \r\n\r\nHowever, you can clean up the tables periodically by running the following cronjob every 3 hours:\r\n\r\n<strong>http://www.yoursite.com/<br class="visible-phone">cometchat/cron.php</strong>\r\n\r\nIf you are using CometService,\r\n\r\nYou can set <strong>"Save Logs"</strong> to <strong>"No"</strong> through <strong>CometChat Administration Panel</strong>.\r\n\r\nClick on <strong>Settings</strong> tab -&gt; <strong>Comet Service</strong> -&gt; Select <strong>"No"</strong> option for <strong>Save logs?</strong> -&gt; Click on <strong>"Update Settings"</strong> button.\r\n', 'I don''t want CometChat to store saved logs. How do I disable the save logs option?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'i-dont-want-cometchat-to-store-saved-logs-how-do-i-disable-the-save-logs-option', '', '', '2013-09-26 10:20:31', '2013-09-26 10:20:31', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=1628', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1668, 1, '2012-08-23 14:38:41', '2012-08-23 09:08:41', 'Yes, you can activate COMET_CHATROOMS (set it to 1) if you have subscribed to <strong>CometService</strong> or any third-party transport in cometchat/config.php file.\n\nWhen using CometService with chatrooms, credits are deducted for every message received and NOT sent. So if there are 20 users in a chatroom and one message is sent, then 20 credits will be used.\n', 'Can I activate CometService for chatrooms?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'can-i-activate-cometservice-for-chatrooms', '', '', '2012-08-23 14:38:41', '2012-08-23 09:08:41', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=1668', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1670, 1, '2012-08-23 14:36:29', '2012-08-23 09:06:29', 'Games are hosted on third-party servers. We do not have any control over the ads being displayed. If you want, you can remove the games plugin completely from CometChat Admin Panel.', 'Do you provide any service to remove the ads from the games?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'do-you-provide-any-service-to-remove-the-ads-from-the-games', '', '', '2012-08-23 14:36:29', '2012-08-23 09:06:29', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=1670', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1714, 1, '2012-08-23 14:40:07', '2012-08-23 09:10:07', 'To change the default display setting of the chat bar to a small clickable bubble icon or to start CometChat in hidden mode:\n\nAdd the following code at the end in the files <strong><em>/cometchat/js/cometchat.js</em></strong> and <strong><em>/cometchat/js/cometchat_lite.js</em></strong> \n\n<pre><code>\njqcc(document).ready(function () {  \n   if(jqcc.cookie(''cc_hidebar'')==null){\n       jqcc(''#cometchat_hide'').click();\n   }\n});\n</code></pre>\n\n<blockquote>Note: Delete all the content of <strong><em>/cometchat/cache/</em></strong> directory and clear your browser cache whenever you make changes in CometChat files manually.</blockquote>', 'How can I disable the full chat bar and change it to display a small clickable bubble icon that activates the chatbar?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'how-can-i-disable-the-full-chat-bar-and-change-it-to-display-a-small-clickable-bubble-icon-that-activates-the-chatbar', '', '', '2012-08-23 14:40:07', '2012-08-23 09:10:07', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=1714', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1911, 1, '2012-10-03 19:40:16', '2012-10-03 14:10:16', '', 'Banned_users', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', 'banned_users', '', '', '2012-10-03 19:40:16', '2012-10-03 14:10:16', '', 0, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/answers/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2012/10/Banned_users.png', 0, 'attachment', 'image/png', 0),
(1923, 1, '2013-04-12 19:24:22', '2013-04-12 13:54:22', 'Yes, changes made to the CometChat settings can be reflected without clearing the browser cache. \n\nTo do so, append a random number to the "href" and "src" attributes of the CometChat''s HTML code as follows:\n\n<pre><code>&lt;link type="text/css" href="/cometchat/cometchatcss.php?ts=random_number" rel="stylesheet" charset="utf-8"&gt;\n&lt;script type="text/javascript" src="/cometchat/cometchatjs.php?ts=random_number" charset="utf-8"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</code></pre>\n\n<strong>Use any random number in place of ''random_number'' in the above code.</strong>', 'How can I avoid forcing my users to clear cache after every change in administration panel?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'how-can-i-avoid-forcing-my-users-to-clear-cache-after-every-change-in-administration-panel', '', '', '2013-04-12 19:24:22', '2013-04-12 13:54:22', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=1923', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1946, 1, '2013-02-08 19:10:28', '2013-02-08 13:40:28', '', 'Facebook Application Settings', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', 'applicationsettings-2', '', '', '2013-02-08 19:10:28', '2013-02-08 13:40:28', '', 0, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/answers/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2013/02/applicationsettings.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(1985, 1, '2013-04-12 19:21:04', '2013-04-12 13:51:04', 'There are 3 options for mobile devices:\n\n<strong>1. CometChat Mobile WebApp</strong> (included in Premium/Platinum Edition)\n\nYour users can login to chat using their mobile browsers. First, they have to login to your site and then can start chatting directly via their browser.\n\n<strong>2. CometChat Native App</strong> (free; available on Apple/Google stores)\n\nYour users can login to chat by simply downloading the app from the store. However, they will be able to see the CometChat branding.\n\n<strong>3. CometChat White-labelled Native App</strong> (sold separately for $399)\n\nWe will completely white-label our native app and upload it under your name in the stores. So the logo, name, icon &amp; price will be customized for your site. Also, the URL bar present in our CometChat Native App will be removed as it will be specific to your site. \nYou can purchase this from: <a href="http://www.cometchat.com/my" title="http://www.cometchat.com/my">http://www.cometchat.com/my</a>\n', 'What is the difference between CometChat App and Mobile Webapp extension?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'what-is-the-difference-between-cometchat-app-and-mobile-webapp-extension', '', '', '2013-04-12 19:21:04', '2013-04-12 13:51:04', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=1985', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1998, 1, '2013-04-12 19:14:04', '2013-04-12 13:44:04', 'In order to use CometChat mobile app with your website, you need to make sure that you are using CometChat <strong>version 5.0.0+</strong>\r\n\r\nAlso, refer to the following steps for troubleshooting any login issues:\r\n\r\n1. If you have white labelled CometChat on your web site, then please use http://&lt;your site URL&gt;/&lt;white labelled name for cometchat&gt;/ as URL.\r\n\r\nfor example:<strong> http://www.mysite.com/<br class="visible-phone">mywhitelabelledcometchat/</strong>\r\n\r\n\r\n2. If you are getting an error message "Username and password do not match" then please make sure you have configured chatLogin function correctly. \r\n\r\nThis function takes username/email and password as input and returns encrypted userID (primary key of your site''s users table) after authenticating user based on your authentication mechanism.\r\n\r\nFor example:\r\n\r\n<pre><code>\r\nfunction chatLogin($userName,$userPass){\r\n	$userid = 0;\r\n	if (filter_var($userName, FILTER_VALIDATE_EMAIL)) {\r\n		$sql ="SELECT * FROM ".TABLE_PREFIX.DB_USERTABLE." WHERE user_email =''".$userName."''";  \r\n	} else {\r\n		$sql ="SELECT * FROM ".TABLE_PREFIX.DB_USERTABLE." WHERE user_loginname =''".$userName."''";\r\n	}	 \r\n	$result=mysql_query($sql);\r\n	$row = mysql_fetch_array($result);		\r\n	\r\n	if($row[''user_password'']== md5($userPass)) {\r\n		$userid = $row[''user_id''];		\r\n	}\r\n	$key = KEY_A.KEY_B.KEY_C;\r\n	return base64_encode(mcrypt_encrypt(MCRYPT_RIJNDAEL_256, md5($key), $userid, MCRYPT_MODE_CBC, md5(md5($key))));\r\n}</code></pre>\r\n\r\n3. Please make sure you have added the following code in getUserID function after <strong>$userid=0;</strong> like:\r\n   <pre><code> if (!empty($_SESSION[''basedata'']) &amp;&amp; $_SESSION[''basedata''] != ''null'') {\r\n		$_REQUEST[''basedata''] = $_SESSION[''basedata''];\r\n	}\r\n	if (!empty($_REQUEST[''basedata'']) &amp;&amp; isset($_REQUEST[''callbackfn'']) &amp;&amp; in_array($_REQUEST[''callbackfn''],array(''desktop'',''mobileapp'')))  {\r\n		$key = KEY_A.KEY_B.KEY_C;\r\n		$uid = rtrim(mcrypt_decrypt(MCRYPT_RIJNDAEL_256, md5($key), base64_decode($_REQUEST[''basedata'']), MCRYPT_MODE_CBC, md5(md5($key))), "");\r\n		if (intval($uid) &gt; 0) {\r\n			$userid = $uid;\r\n		}\r\n	}</code></pre>', 'How do I get my website working with the CometChat App for iPhone and Android?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'how-do-i-get-my-cometchat-working-with-the-cometchat-app-for-iphone-and-android', '', '', '2013-09-26 10:19:56', '2013-09-26 10:19:56', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=1998', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1999, 1, '2013-09-23 09:26:26', '2013-09-23 09:26:26', 'Welcome to <a href="http://v6.cometchat.com/">CometChat Sites</a>. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start blogging!', 'Hello world!', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 09:26:26', '2013-09-23 09:26:26', '', 1, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/answers/2013/09/23/1-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
