(4658, 1, '2013-09-23 12:21:08', '2013-09-23 12:21:08', '<h4>Introduction</h4>\r\n\r\nThis guide will help you through the installation process and get CometChat running on your site.\r\n\r\nInstallation is very straight forward, only taking about 30 minutes from uploading the files to viewing the CometChat bar on your site.\r\n\r\nBefore you begin, you will need an FTP client, if you do not have one, some popular solutions include [FileZilla](http://filezilla-project.org/) (free) or [CuteFTP](http://www.globalscape.com/products/ftp_clients.aspx) (trial).\r\n\r\nThis guide assumes that you have successfully downloaded the latest release of CometChat and have the zip file "unzipped" and ready to go. If not, you can download the package from your client area.\r\n\r\nThe instructions will term the zip file you downloaded as *cometchat.zip*.\r\n\r\n<h4> Uploading</h4>\r\n\r\nAt this point, you should have the zip archive cometchat.zip and find a single folder- "cometchat".\r\n\r\nIf you access your site via ''http://www.domain.com'', then look for the webroot directory.\r\n\r\nThe "webroot" directory is usually ''public_html'' or ''www'', but this varies from server to server so if you''re unsure, contact your hosting provider.\r\n\r\nUsing your FTP client, copy the cometchat folder to your webroot directory. e.g. http://www.domain.com/cometchat\r\n\r\n<h4> Configuration</h4>\r\n\r\n*Switch on development mode*\r\n \r\nEdit config.php and search for the tag:\r\n\r\n	/* ADVANCED */\r\n\r\nSet **DEV_MODE** to 1 and **ERROR_LOGGING** to 1. After integration, you can set these to 0.\r\n\r\n	define(''DEV_MODE'',''1'');\r\n	define(''ERROR_LOGGING'',''1'');\r\n\r\n*Add your database information*\r\n\r\nEdit *integration.php* and update the DATABASE details.\r\n\r\n	/* DATABASE */\r\n	\r\n	define(''DB_SERVER'',''localhost'');\r\n	define(''DB_PORT'',''3306'');\r\n	define(''DB_USERNAME'',''root'');\r\n	define(''DB_PASSWORD'',''password'');\r\n	define(''DB_NAME'',''databasename'');\r\n	define(''TABLE_PREFIX'','''');\r\n	define(''DB_USERTABLE'',''users'');\r\n	define(''DB_USERTABLE_NAME'',''username'');\r\n	define(''DB_USERTABLE_USERID'',''userid'');\r\n	define(''DB_USERTABLE_LASTACTIVITY'',''lastactivity'');\r\n	define(''DB_AVATARTABLE''," ");\r\n	define(''DB_AVATARFIELD''," ".TABLE_PREFIX.DB_USERTABLE.".".DB_USERTABLE_USERID." ");\r\n\r\nThe first 5 lines are used to access the database. You must access your existing database and not create a separate database for CometChat.\r\n\r\nThe next 7 lines specify details about your database schema.\r\n\r\n* If all your tables use a prefix, for example cc_, then specify the *TABLE_PREFIX* as cc_\r\n* *DB_USERTABLE* specifies the name of the table in which your user information is stored.\r\n* *DB_USERTABLE_NAME* specifies the name of the field in which the user''s name/display name is stored.\r\n* *DB_USERTABLE_USERID* specifies the name of the field in which the user''s id is stored (usually id or userid or user_id or member_id). This field must be of integer type.\r\n* *DB_AVATARTABLE* specifies join of users table with avatar table. If avatar is stored in the users table then leave this field blank.\r\n* *DB_AVATARFIELD* is the user ID by default. You can change this if your site stores avatar in users or avatars table.\r\n\r\n \r\nThe code will look like:\r\n\r\n	define(''TABLE_PREFIX'',''tableprefix_'');\r\n	define(''DB_USERTABLE'',''userstable'');\r\n	define(''DB_USERTABLE_NAME'',''username'');\r\n	define(''DB_USERTABLE_USERID'',''userid'');\r\n	define(''DB_AVATARTABLE''," ");\r\n	define(''DB_AVATARFIELD''," ".TABLE_PREFIX.DB_USERTABLE.".".DB_USERTABLE_USERID." ");\r\n\r\nIn order to keep track of which users are online, CometChat makes use of an integer field which stores a UNIX timestamp (which is an INTEGER) of the user''s last activity. If you do not have such a field in your user''s table as yet, you can execute the following SQL command:\r\n\r\n	ALTER TABLE users ADD lastactivity INTEGER DEFAULT 0; // Update "users" to your users'' table name\r\n\r\n*Update single-sign-on functionality*\r\n\r\nScroll down to find the getUserID() function.\r\n\r\nThe getUserID() function is used to return the logged in user''s ID. Depending on how you have programmed your site, you will have to find out the user''s ID.\r\n\r\nIf you have written a simple PHP authentication, then during the authentication, you can specify a session variable like:\r\n\r\n	/* In your own login.php */\r\n	/* After you authenticate the user */\r\n	$_SESSION[''userid''] = $users[''id'']; // Modify to suit requirements\r\n\r\nThen your getUserID() function will look like:\r\n \r\n	function getUserID() {\r\n		$userid = 0; // Return 0 if user is not logged in\r\n		\r\n		if (!empty($_SESSION[''userid''])) {\r\n			$userid = $_SESSION[''userid''];\r\n		}\r\n	\r\n		return $userid;\r\n	}\r\n\r\nIf you are using a cookie then read that using the following function:\r\n\r\n	function getUserID() {\r\n		$userid = 0; // Return 0 if user is not logged in\r\n		\r\n		if (!empty($_COOKIE[''userid''])) {\r\n			$userid = $_COOKIE[''userid''];\r\n		}\r\n	\r\n		return $userid;\r\n	}\r\n\r\nIf you are using a more complex method of authentication like storing the session_hash in the database, then your getUserID() function will look something like:\r\n\r\n	function getUserID() {\r\n		$userid = 0; // Return 0 if user is not logged in\r\n	\r\n	        if (!empty($_COOKIE[''sessionhash''])) {\r\n		    $sql = ("select userid from ".TABLE_PREFIX."session \r\n	            where sessionhash = ''".mysql_real_escape_string($_COOKIE[''sessionhash''])."''");\r\n		    $query = mysql_query($sql);\r\n		    $session = mysql_fetch_array($query);\r\n		    $userid = $session[''userid''];\r\n	        }\r\n	\r\n		return $userid;\r\n	}\r\n\r\n*Update Who''s Online list fetching mechanism*\r\n\r\nWe modify the getFriendsList() function.\r\n\r\nThe getFriendsList() function returns all the users'' details part of the Who''s Online list. This list need not necessarily be friends of the logged in user. It may simply be all online users instead. You can customize this to return any set of users.\r\n\r\nThe default configuration assumes that you have a table called friends with the following fields:\r\n\r\n	toid integer\r\n	fromid integer\r\n\r\n All entries are assumed to be two-way i.e. if user A (id:1) and user B (id:2) are friends, then there will be two entries in the table:\r\n\r\n	----------------------------\r\n	 id    toid    fromid\r\n	----------------------------\r\n	 13       1         2\r\n	 14       2         1\r\n	----------------------------\r\n	\r\nYour getFriendsList() will look like:\r\n	\r\n	function getFriendsList($userid,$time) {\r\n		$sql = ("select DISTINCT ".TABLE_PREFIX.DB_USERTABLE.".".DB_USERTABLE_USERID." userid, ".TABLE_PREFIX.DB_USERTABLE.".".DB_USERTABLE_NAME." username, \r\n	".TABLE_PREFIX.DB_USERTABLE.".".DB_USERTABLE_LASTACTIVITY." lastactivity, \r\n	".DB_AVATARFIELD." avatar, ".TABLE_PREFIX.DB_USERTABLE.".".DB_USERTABLE_USERID." link, \r\n	cometchat_status.message, cometchat_status.status \r\n	from ".TABLE_PREFIX."friends join ".TABLE_PREFIX.DB_USERTABLE." on  ".TABLE_PREFIX."friends.toid = ".TABLE_PREFIX.DB_USERTABLE.".".DB_USERTABLE_USERID." left join 			cometchat_status on ".TABLE_PREFIX.DB_USERTABLE.".".DB_USERTABLE_USERID." = cometchat_status.userid ".DB_AVATARTABLE."\r\n	 where ".TABLE_PREFIX."friends.fromid = ''".mysql_real_escape_string($userid)."'' order by username asc");\r\n		return $sql;\r\n	}\r\n\r\n If you would like to show all online users instead, then you can use an SQL query like:\r\n \r\n	function getFriendsList($userid,$time) {\r\n		$sql = ("select DISTINCT ".TABLE_PREFIX.DB_USERTABLE.".".DB_USERTABLE_USERID." userid, \r\n	".TABLE_PREFIX.DB_USERTABLE.".".DB_USERTABLE_NAME." username, ".TABLE_PREFIX.DB_USERTABLE.".".DB_USERTABLE_LASTACTIVITY." lastactivity, \r\n	".DB_AVATARFIELD." avatar, ".TABLE_PREFIX.DB_USERTABLE.".".DB_USERTABLE_USERID." link, cometchat_status.message, cometchat_status.status from 	".TABLE_PREFIX.DB_USERTABLE." left join cometchat_status on ".TABLE_PREFIX.DB_USERTABLE.".".DB_USERTABLE_USERID." = cometchat_status.userid ".DB_AVATARTABLE." \r\n	where ".TABLE_PREFIX.DB_USERTABLE.".".DB_USERTABLE_USERID."  ''".mysql_real_escape_string($userid)."'' and (''".mysql_real_escape_string($time)."''- 	".TABLE_PREFIX.DB_USERTABLE.".".DB_USERTABLE_LASTACTIVITY." &lt; &#039;&quot;.((ONLINE_TIMEOUT)*2).&quot;&#039;) and (cometchat_status.status IS NULL OR cometchat_status.status  ''invisible'' OR 	cometchat_status.status  ''offline'') order by username asc");\r\n		return $sql;\r\n	}\r\n\r\n*Update status message, avatar and links functionality*\r\n\r\nThe getUserStatus() function returns the current status message as well as state of the user (available, busy, invisible, offline). If your site already has a status updates feature, then you will have to modify the first field- cometchat_status.message which is returned to pull the status message from your table.\r\n\r\nFinally, we modify getLink() and getAvatar() function\r\n\r\nWhen the getFriendsList() function is executed, avatar and link contain the user id by default (you can change this if you store the avatar/link location in your table). getLink() and getAvatar() functions are used to post-process the data obtained from the getFriendsList() function.\r\n\r\nFor example:\r\n\r\n	function getLink($link) {\r\n	    return ''users.php?id=''.$link;\r\n	}\r\n	\r\n	function getAvatar($image) {\r\n	    if (is_file(dirname(dirname(__FILE__)).''/images/''.$image.''.gif'')) {\r\n	        return ''/images/''.$image.''.gif'';\r\n	    } else {\r\n	        return ''/images/noavatar.gif'';\r\n	    }\r\n	}\r\n\r\nThe hooks_statusupdate() function is called when a user updates his/her status via CometChat. If your site already has a status updates feature, you can update that using this hook.\r\n\r\n<h4> Installation </h4>\r\n\r\n* Step 1\r\n\r\nYou should now run the installer file through your web browser by entering the URL to it into your browser address bar (if you have followed our example, type in http://www.domain.com/cometchat/install.php, naturally substituting ''domain.com'' for your web address).\r\n\r\nIf the installation was completed successfully, then two lines of HTML code will be displayed on your screen. Please copy these two lines.\r\n\r\n* Step 2\r\n\r\nNow edit your template header.\r\n\r\nImmediately after the opening head tag add the copied code\r\n\r\nNow delete install.php file from the cometchat folder.\r\n\r\nThat''s all! Now log-in to your site and you will be able to see the CometChat bar. For customizing the text, icons, plugins, theme and modules, please refer to other documents.', 'Custom PHP Site', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '177-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:21:08', '2013-09-23 12:21:08', '', 177, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/177-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4659, 1, '2013-09-23 12:22:50', '2013-09-23 12:22:50', 'The installation instructions are the same as that of Custom PHP Site. However, before proceeding to them, please make sure that you have configured your server.\r\n\r\n*No modifications are required to your existing ASP or .NET site code.*\r\n\r\n&gt; Please create a support ticket for the PHP + MSSQL version of CometChat. The default adapter is PHP + mySQL.\r\n\r\n<h4> Server Setup</h4>\r\n\r\n* Install *PHP* on your IIS server using the tool at [http://php.iis.net](http://php.iis.net)\r\n* Install the *SQLSRV* driver for PHP to allow PHP to connect to MSSQL from [http://www.microsoft.com/sqlserver/2005/en/us/php-driver.aspx](http://www.microsoft.com/sqlserver/2005/en/us/php-driver.aspx)\r\n\r\n<h4> Code Modification</h4>\r\n\r\nThe only modification that needs to be performed in your existing ASP or .NET code is to add a cookie like *userid* when the user logs in and reset it to 0 when the user logs out.\r\n\r\n<h4> Follow Custom PHP Site Instructions</h4>\r\n\r\nOnce that above is completed, follow the installation instructions for [custom PHP site](http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/installing-cometchat/custom-coded-site/php-site).', 'Custom ASP or .NET Site', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '179-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:22:50', '2013-09-23 12:22:50', '', 179, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/179-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4660, 1, '2013-09-23 12:23:56', '2013-09-23 12:23:56', 'The installation instructions are the same as that of Custom PHP Site. However, before proceeding to them, please make sure that you have configured your server.\r\n\r\n*No modifications are required to your existing ColdFusion site code.*\r\n\r\n&gt; Please create a support ticket if you are using MSSQL server. The default adapter is PHP + mySQL.\r\n\r\n<h4> Code Modification</h4>\r\n\r\nThe only modification that needs to be performed in your existing cF code is to add a cookie like *userid* when the user logs in and reset it to 0 when the user logs out. Then CometChat can use this cookie to read the logged in user''s ID.\r\n\r\n<h4> Follow hosting CometChat on a separate server instructions</h4>\r\n\r\nFollow the installation instructions for [CometChat on separate server](http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/tutorials/hosting-cometchat-on-a-separate-server).\r\n\r\n<h4> Follow Custom PHP site instructions</h4>\r\n\r\nOnce that above is completed, follow the installation instructions for [custom PHP site](http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/installing-cometchat/custom-coded-site/php-site).', 'Custom ColdFusion Site', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '183-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:23:56', '2013-09-23 12:23:56', '', 183, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/183-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4661, 1, '2013-09-23 12:25:12', '2013-09-23 12:25:12', 'The installation instructions are the same as that of Custom PHP Site. However, before proceeding to them, please make sure that you have configured your server.\r\n\r\n*No modifications are required to your existing Java or JSP site code.*\r\n\r\n<h4> Code Modification</h4>\r\n\r\nThe only modification that needs to be performed in your existing code is to add a cookie like *userid* when the user logs in and reset it to 0 when the user logs out. Then CometChat can use this cookie to read the logged in user''s ID.\r\n\r\n<h4> Follow hosting CometChat on a separate server instructions</h4>\r\n\r\nFollow the installation instructions for [CometChat on separate server](http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/tutorials/hosting-cometchat-on-a-separate-server).\r\n\r\n<h4> Follow Custom PHP site instructions</h4>\r\n\r\nOnce that above is completed, follow the installation instructions for [custom PHP site](http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/installing-cometchat/custom-coded-site/php-site).', 'Custom Java or JSP Site', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '181-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:25:12', '2013-09-23 12:25:12', '', 181, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/181-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4662, 1, '2013-09-23 12:25:46', '2013-09-23 12:25:46', 'The installation instructions are the same as that of Custom PHP Site. However, before proceeding to them, please make sure that you have configured your server.\r\n\r\n*No modifications are required to your existing Ruby on Rails site code.*\r\n\r\n<h4> Code Modification</h4>\r\n\r\nThe only modification that needs to be performed in your existing code is to add a cookie like *userid* when the user logs in and reset it to 0 when the user logs out. Then CometChat can use this cookie to read the logged in user''s ID.\r\n\r\n<h4> Follow hosting CometChat on a separate server instructions</h4>\r\n\r\nFollow the installation instructions for [CometChat on separate server](http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/tutorials/hosting-cometchat-on-a-separate-server).\r\n\r\n<h4>Follow Custom PHP site instructions</h4>\r\n\r\nOnce that above is completed, follow the installation instructions for [custom PHP site](http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/installing-cometchat/custom-coded-site/php-site).', 'Custom Ruby on Rails Site', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '185-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:25:46', '2013-09-23 12:25:46', '', 185, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/185-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4663, 1, '2013-09-23 12:28:55', '2013-09-23 12:28:55', '&gt; We strongly recommend that you back up your site prior to any upgrade. Upgrading will reset all your settings. All changes made in your previous edition will have to be re-performed.\n\n<h4> Upgrading to a newer version (e.g. 2.0.5 to 3.0.1)</h4>\n\nCometChat can be upgraded using the following steps.\n\n1. Rename your existing *cometchat* folder to *cometchat_old*\n2. Upload the new *cometchat* folder\n3. Point your browser to http://www.yoursite.com/cometchat/install.php\n\n*Warning*: Do not copy config.php from the older installation to your new version. You will have to re-do all the configuration settings from CometChat Administration Panel.\n\n<h4> Upgrading to a higher edition but different version</h4>\n\nFollow the same instructions as upgrading to a newer version\n\n<h4>Upgrading to a higher edition for same version (e.g. Basic to Professional Edition)</h4>\n\n1. Update the *cometchat/license.php* file\n2. Upload the new *plugins* as per your requirements', 'Upgrading CometChat', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '172-autosave-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:28:55', '2013-09-23 12:28:55', '', 172, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/172-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4664, 1, '2013-09-23 12:28:58', '2013-09-23 12:28:58', '&gt; We strongly recommend that you back up your site prior to any upgrade. Upgrading will reset all your settings. All changes made in your previous edition will have to be re-performed.\r\n\r\n<h4> Upgrading to a newer version (e.g. 2.0.5 to 3.0.1)</h4>\r\n\r\nCometChat can be upgraded using the following steps.\r\n\r\n1. Rename your existing *cometchat* folder to *cometchat_old*\r\n2. Upload the new *cometchat* folder\r\n3. Point your browser to http://www.yoursite.com/cometchat/install.php\r\n\r\n*Warning*: Do not copy config.php from the older installation to your new version. You will have to re-do all the configuration settings from CometChat Administration Panel.\r\n\r\n<h4> Upgrading to a higher edition but different version</h4>\r\n\r\nFollow the same instructions as upgrading to a newer version\r\n\r\n<h4>Upgrading to a higher edition for same version (e.g. Basic to Professional Edition)</h4>\r\n\r\n1. Update the *cometchat/license.php* file\r\n2. Upload the new *plugins* as per your requirements', 'Upgrading CometChat', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '172-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:28:58', '2013-09-23 12:28:58', '', 172, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/172-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4665, 1, '2013-09-23 12:30:10', '2013-09-23 12:30:10', '<h4>Getting Started</h4>\r\n\r\nThe administration panel can be accessed at http://www.yoursite.com/cometchat/admin\r\n\r\nThe first thing you will see is a prompt to login to access the administration panel. This username and password is different from your site’s login details.\r\n\r\n![Login Details](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/03/login.png "login")	\r\n\r\n#Default Username/Password	\r\nBy default, the username and password are as follows:\r\n\r\nUsername:*cometchat*		\r\nPassword:*cometchat*		\r\n\r\nAfter you login, you will be taken to the dashboard which will show you statistics of CometChat on your site.\r\n\r\n![dashboard](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/03/dasboard.png "dashboard")', 'Log In to the Admin Panel', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '56-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:30:10', '2013-09-23 12:30:10', '', 56, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/56-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4666, 1, '2013-09-23 12:31:38', '2013-09-23 12:31:38', '<h4> Modules add new functionality to the CometChat bar.</h4>\r\n\r\n![Modules]\r\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/04/Capture6.png)\r\n\r\n<h4> Live Modules</h4>\r\n\r\nYou can use your mouse to change the order in which the modules appear on the bar (left-to-right).\r\n\r\nThe center section displays all active modules. \r\nOn the right hand side, the *Available Modules* shows the ready modules that you can integrate instantly.\r\n\r\nTo integrate a module, simply click on the *add* button. The selected module will be displayed in the center section.\r\n\r\n![Modules - Live Modules]\r\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/04/new+live+modules.png)', 'Modules', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '132-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:31:38', '2013-09-23 12:31:38', '', 132, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/132-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4667, 1, '2013-09-23 12:32:49', '2013-09-23 12:32:49', 'You can easily generate iframe codes, remove an existing module, open a module in lightbox/pop ups or display the title for different modules in your website with the help of different options available in the center section.  \r\n\r\n![annotationsfinal]\r\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/05/annotationsfinal.png)\r\n\r\n<h4> Show/Hide title of a module</h4>\r\n\r\nTo show the title of any module in the chat bar, click on the ***Show/Hide Title*** button of the respective Module.\r\n\r\n![Show module titles]\r\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/05/Show+module+titles.png)\r\n\r\nTo hide the titles of these modules, click on the same button.\r\n\r\n![Hide module title]\r\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/05/hide+modules+titles.png)\r\n\r\n<h4> Open module in a light-box/popup</h4>\r\n\r\nTo open a module in a light box, click on the ***Light Box*** button.\r\nWith this feature, the selected module will appear as a *light box*. You can drag this light box anywhere on your screen. \r\n\r\n![Translate Conversation Lightbox]\r\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/05/Translate+Conversation+Lightbox.png)\r\n\r\nTo set the module as a *popup*, click on the same button.\r\n\r\n![Translate Conversation Popup]\r\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/05/Translate+Conversation+Popup.png)\r\n\r\n<h4> Embed Module into your site</h4>\r\n\r\nClick on the ***Generate Embed Code*** button, next to the module that you would like to embed.\r\n\r\nFor example:-	\r\n\r\n* Click on the *Generate Embed Code* button of the **‘Games’** module.	 \r\n* A window pops out with the *iframe HTML code*.	\r\n* Copy the code and add to your site page.	\r\n\r\n ![embed link1]\r\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/05/embed+link1.png)\r\n\r\n* Now the Game Module will be visible on your site’s page.	\r\n\r\n![Embed game module]\r\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/05/abc.png)\r\n\r\n<h4>Configure Module</h4>\r\n\r\nWith this option you can change the setting of any module.\r\n\r\nTo configure a module, click on the *Configure Module* button. A window pops out where you can change the settings of a module accordingly.\r\n\r\nFor example:-\r\n\r\n* To configure the **Chatrooms module**, click on the *Configure Module* button.	\r\n* Set the values for the chatroom settings	\r\n* Then click on the *Update Settings* button.\r\n\r\n![Modules - Settings]\r\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/04/chatroom+modules.png)\r\n\r\nSimilarly, configuration can be done for Games, Facebook Fan Page, Twitter and Translate Conversation modules.\r\n\r\n<h4> Remove Module</h4>\r\n\r\nClick on the *Remove Module* button to remove a module from the chat bar', 'Configuring Modules', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '814-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:32:49', '2013-09-23 12:32:49', '', 814, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/814-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4668, 1, '2013-09-23 12:33:31', '2013-09-23 12:33:31', '<h4> Creating a Facebook Fan Page</h4>\r\n\r\nTo create a page, point your browser to [http://www.facebook.com/pages/create.php](http://www.facebook.com/pages/create.php)\r\n\r\n![Facebook - Create Fan Page](http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/media/6.png)\r\n\r\n&gt; CometChat does not allow use of Facebook Groups. You must create a Facebook Fan Page.\r\n\r\n<h4> Configuring the module</h4>\r\n\r\nOn creation of a Facebook Fan Page, you will need to find your Facebook Fan Page ID.\r\n\r\nClick on the *Edit Page* link on your Facebook Fan Page and pay attention to the browser URL.\r\n\r\n![Facebook - Fan Page ID](http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/media/7.png)\r\n\r\nIn the above example, the Facebook Page ID is *106148049425133*\r\n\r\nOnce you have located your Page ID, go to *CometChat Administration Panel* -&gt; *Modules* -&gt; *Facebook Fan Page* -&gt; *config*\r\n\r\nEnter your Page ID in the *Facebook Fan Page ID* and empty the *Facebook Fan Page Name* box. Finally click on the *Update Settings* button.\r\n\r\n![CometChat - Facebook Fan Page](http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/media/8.png)', 'Facebook Fan Page', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '138-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:33:31', '2013-09-23 12:33:31', '', 138, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/138-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4669, 1, '2013-09-23 12:34:02', '2013-09-23 12:34:02', '<h4> Configuring the module</h4>\r\n\r\nTo configure this module, set the values of the chatroom settings according to your requirements and then click on the *Update Settings* button.\r\n\r\n![Chatroom Modules]\r\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/04/chatroom+modules.png)', 'Chatrooms', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1224-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:34:02', '2013-09-23 12:34:02', '', 1224, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/1224-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4670, 1, '2013-09-23 12:34:43', '2013-09-23 12:34:43', '<h4>Selecting between Google and Microsoft</h4>\r\n\r\nCometChat''s real-time translate feature can integrate with either Microsoft''s Translate API or Google''s Translate API. Below are the pricing details for each service:\r\n\r\n[Microsoft''s Translate API](http://go.microsoft.com/?linkid=9782667) (includes free plan)\r\n\r\n[Google''s Translate API](http://code.google.com/apis/language/translate/v2/pricing.html) (only $20 for 1 million characters)\r\n\r\nOnce you have decided which API you would like to use, please follow the instructions accordingly:\r\n\r\n<h4>Configuring Microsoft''s Translate API</h4>\r\n\r\nYou need to sign up for the *Microsoft Translator* service. Depending on your requirements, you can select a *Subscription*.\r\n\r\n[Microsoft''s Translate API Signup](http://go.microsoft.com/?linkid=9782667)\r\n\r\n![Microsoft''s Translate API Signup](http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/media/21.png)\r\n\r\nAfter completing the signup, you need to register your application at [https://datamarket.azure.com/developer/applications/](https://datamarket.azure.com/developer/applications/)\r\n\r\nMake sure that your Client ID and Client Secret are unique values. Sample information:\r\n\r\n![Register your applicat](http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/media/22.png)\r\n\r\nOnce this is done, you need to configure the module.\r\n\r\nGo to *CometChat Administration Panel* -&gt; *Modules* -&gt; *Real-time Translate* -&gt; *config*\r\n\r\nEnter your *Client ID* and *Client Secret* values which you filled earlier. Finally click on *Update Settings* button.\r\n\r\n![Real-time Translate Settings](http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/media/23.png)\r\n\r\nThen simply clear your browser cache and test the real-time translate feature with another user.\r\n\r\n<h4>Configuring Google''s Translate API</h4>\r\n\r\nYou need to sign up for the *Translate API* service.\r\n\r\n[Google''s Translate API Signup](https://code.google.com/apis/console)\r\n\r\nOn login, go to the *Services* tab and activate *Translate API*\r\n\r\n![Google''s Translate API Signup](http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/media/24.png)\r\n\r\nNow, go to the *Billng* tab and make sure billing is enabled. Without adding this information, Google Translate will not work.\r\n\r\nGo to the *API access* tab and copy the *API key* from the *Simple API Access* section.\r\n\r\n![Google''s Translate API Key](http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/media/25.png)\r\n\r\nGo to *CometChat Administration Panel* -&gt; *Modules* -&gt; *Real-time Translate* -&gt; *config*\r\n\r\nLeave the *Client ID* and *Client Secret* values as blank, set *Use Google Translate API* to *Yes* and add the key which you copied earlier. Finally click on *Update Settings* button.\r\n\r\n![Real-time Translate Settings](http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/media/26.png)\r\n\r\nThen simply clear your browser cache and test the real-time translate feature with another user.\r\n', 'Real-time Translate', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '585-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:34:43', '2013-09-23 12:34:43', '', 585, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/585-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4671, 1, '2013-09-23 12:35:08', '2013-09-23 12:35:08', '<h4>Creating a Twitter account</h4>\r\n\r\nTo create a Twitter account, point your browser to [http://www.twitter.com](http://www.twitter.com)\r\n\r\n![Twitter - Create New Account](http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/media/9.png)\r\n\r\n<h4> Configuring the module</h4>\r\n\r\nOnce you have your Twitter username, go to *CometChat Administration Panel* -&gt; *Modules* -&gt; *Twitter* -&gt; *config*\r\n\r\nEnter your username in the *Twitter Username* and set *No of Followers* to *48* and *No of Tweet* to *12*. Finally click on *Update Settings* button.\r\n\r\n![CometChat - Twitter](http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/media/10.png)', 'Twitter', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '140-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:35:08', '2013-09-23 12:35:08', '', 140, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/140-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4672, 1, '2013-09-23 12:35:43', '2013-09-23 12:35:43', '<h4>Overview</h4>\r\n\r\nPlugins are of two types:\r\n\r\n1. To enhance one-on-one chat functionality\r\n2. To enhance chatroom functionality\r\n\r\n<h4>One-on-one chat plugins</h4>\r\n\r\nOne-on-one chat plugins add new features to the one-on-one chat box. In other words, when the user of your site chats with another user using the chat box on the right side, he/she can have a better chatting experience with the help of these plugins \r\ne.g. audio/video chat, screen-sharing etc. are examples of one-on-one chat.\r\n\r\n<h4> Chatroom plugins</h4>\r\n\r\nChatroom plugins add new functionality to chat rooms. You can add plugins like video conference, screen-sharing, white-board etc. to chatrooms. All plugins available for one-on-one chat cannot be added to chatrooms but most plugins are common with one difference. In one-on-one chat, these plugins are used between two users. In chatrooms, they are used by multiple users at the same time.', 'Plugins', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '62-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:35:43', '2013-09-23 12:35:43', '', 62, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/62-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4673, 1, '2013-09-23 12:36:11', '2013-09-23 12:36:11', '<h4>One-on-One Plugins</h4>\r\n\r\nTo activate one-on-one plugins, you need to go to *CometChat Admin Panel -&gt; Plugins*\r\n\r\nThe center panel shows plugins that are currently live on your site and available plugins shows the list of plugins that you can add to CometChat. To change the order, you can simply move the plugins vertically.\r\n\r\n![Plugins1]\r\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/04/pluginnew1.png)\r\n\r\n<h4>Chatroom Plugins</h4>\r\n\r\nTo activate chatroom plugins, you need to go to *CometChat Admin Panel -&gt; Plugins -&gt; Chatroom plugins*.\r\n\r\nChatroom plugins must be configured using the One-on-One plugins page. There is no configuration option in the chatroom plugins page.\r\n\r\n![Chatroom - Plugins]\r\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/04/Chat+plguins1.png)\r\n\r\n&gt; Clear your browser cache completely to view changes after any modifications. Your browser may cache the output of the JS file and thus you may not be able to view the added plugins until you clear your browser cache.', 'Activating Plugins', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '64-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:36:11', '2013-09-23 12:36:11', '', 64, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/64-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4674, 1, '2013-09-23 12:37:01', '2013-09-23 12:37:01', 'If you would like to self-host Adobe FMS server,		\r\n\r\n* Purchase, download and install Adobe FMS on your server (outside support scope)		\r\n\r\nIf you would like to use a third-party Adobe FMS host,		\r\n\r\n* Sign up with a host like [http://www.influxis.com/](http://www.influxis.com/)		\r\n\r\n<h4>Installing Audio/Video Broadcast Plugin with FMS</h4>\r\n	\r\nCreate a folder named ‘*avbroadcast*’ in the applications directory of your FMS.\r\n\r\nFor example, if you are using FMS v4.5 on windows system then you need to create the *avbroadcast* folder in ‘*C:Program FilesAdobeFlash Media Server 4.5applications*'' folder.		\r\n\r\n<h4>Configuring the Audio/Video Broadcast Plugin</h4>		\r\n\r\n* In the *CometChat Admin Panel* -&gt; *Plugins* section, add the *Audio/Video Broadcast Plugin* to your live plugins and click on the *config* link besides the name.	\r\n\r\n* Enter the required details.		\r\n\r\n* Click on the *Update Settings* button and close the window.		\r\n\r\n![Broadcast Setting](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/03/broadcast_3.png)', 'FMS (RTMFP)', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '4344-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:37:01', '2013-09-23 12:37:01', '', 4344, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/4344-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4675, 1, '2013-09-23 12:38:55', '2013-09-23 12:38:55', '<h4>RED5</h4>\r\n\r\nIf you would like to self-host RED5 server,	\r\n	\r\n* Point your browser to [http://www.red5.org/](http://www.red5.org/)	\r\n	\r\n* Download and install **Red5 1.0 RC1** on your server from the following link: [http://code.google.com/p/red5/](http://code.google.com/p/red5/)	\r\n(outside support scope)		\r\n\r\nIf you would like to use a third-party Red5 host,	\r\n		\r\n* Sign up with a host like [http://www.red5host.com/](http://www.red5host.com/)		\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4>Installing Audio/Video Chat Plugin with RED5 server</h4>\r\n\r\n* If you don''t have Red5 installed on your server, click the following link:	\r\n[Steps to install Red5 along with server side packages of CometChat plugins on your server](http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/tutorials/installing-red5)		\r\n\r\n* If you have Red5 up and running on your server, configure CometChat plugins by following the steps listed below:\r\n\r\n*On Linux based systems :*\r\n\r\n1. Check whether the Red5 server is up and running by visiting the URL: *http://&lt;red5 server URL or IP&gt;:5080*	\r\n\r\n2. If the Red5 server is running successfully then go to to webapps directory of your Red5 installation. If RED5 is installed using SVN then in most of the cases the webapp directory is **red5_&lt;version&gt;.svn/dist/webapps**.\r\n\r\n3. Download the sever side package for the required plugin by executing the following command: 	\r\n**wget http://www.cometchat.com/extra/ccred5avchat.tar.gz**	\r\n\r\n4. Run the given command to extract the package: **tar -xzf ccred5avchat.tar.gz**	\r\n\r\n5. Then delete the tar file by executing the given command: **rm ccred5avchat.tar.gz**	\r\n\r\n6. Finally restart the Red5 server.\r\n7. Thus you have successfully configured Red5 server with server side packages of CometChat plugins on your Linux Systems and now you can test the AVChat plugin on your site.\r\n\r\n*On Windows server :*\r\n\r\n1. Check whether the Red5 server is up and running by visiting the URL: *http://&lt;red5 server URL or IP&gt;:5080*	\r\n\r\n2. If the Red5 server is running successfully then download the sever side package for the required plugin from *http://www.cometchat.com/extra/ccred5avchat.zip*	\r\n\r\n3. Unzip the ccred5avchat.zip file and move the avchat folder to **webapps** folder of Red5 installation.		\r\n\r\n4. Finally restart the Red5 server.\r\n5. Thus you have successfully configured Red5 server with server side packages of CometChat plugins on your Windows Server and now you can test the AVChat plugin on your site.\r\n\r\n<h4>Adobe FMS</h4>\r\n\r\nIf you would like to self-host Adobe FMS server,\r\n\r\n* Purchase, download and install Adobe FMS on your server (outside support scope)		\r\n\r\nIf you would like to use a third-party Adobe FMS host,\r\n\r\n* Sign up with a host like [http://www.influxis.com/](http://www.influxis.com/)\r\n\r\n<h4>Installing Audio/Video Chat Plugin with FMS</h4>\r\n\r\nCreate a folder named **‘avchat’** in the applications directory of your FMS.\r\n\r\nFor example, if you are using FMS v4.5 on windows system then you need to create the **avchat** folder in *‘C:Program FilesAdobeFlash Media Server 4.5applications‘* folder.\r\n\r\n<h4>Configuring the Audio/Video Chat Plugin</h4>\r\n\r\n* In the **CometChat Admin Panel** -&gt; Plugins section, add the **Audio/Video Chat Plugin** to your live plugins and click on the **config** link besides the name.	\r\n\r\n* Enter the required details.	\r\n\r\n* Click on the **Update Settings** button and close the window.\r\n\r\n![Red5 or FMS]\r\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/06/red5+or+fms-e1339765753310.png)', 'RED5 or FMS (RTMP)', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2946-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:38:55', '2013-09-23 12:38:55', '', 2946, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/2946-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4676, 1, '2013-09-23 12:39:18', '2013-09-23 12:39:18', '<h4> Configuring Report Conversation Plugin</h4>\r\n\r\nTo receive the incident reports from your users, enter your *Email Address* and click on the *Update Settings* button.\r\n\r\n![Report Conversation Setting]\r\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/04/Report+Conversation+Setting1.png)', 'Report Conversation Plugin', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1040-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:39:18', '2013-09-23 12:39:18', '', 1040, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/1040-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4677, 1, '2013-09-23 12:41:42', '2013-09-23 12:41:42', '<h4>Activating Screensharing Plugin</h4>\n\nScreensharing plugin is one of the few plugins which requires a third-party service. Screensharing can use RED5, Adobe FMS or AddLive.	\n\n<h4>Use RED5 server</h4>		\n\nIf you would like to self-host RED5 server,		\n\n* Point your browser to [http://www.red5.org/](http://www.red5.org/)		\n\n* Download and install Red5 1.0 RC1 on your server from the following link: [http://code.google.com/p/red5/](https://code.google.com/p/red5/)\n(outside support scope)		\n\nIf you would like to use a third-party Red5 host,		\n\n* Sign up with a host like, [http://www.red5host.com/](http://www.red5host.com/)		\n\n<h4>Installing Screensharing Plugin with RED5 server</h4>	\n* If you don’t have Red5 installed on your server, click the following link:		\n[Steps to install Red5 along with server side packages of CometChat plugins on your server](http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/tutorials/installing-red5)		\n\n* If you have Red5 up and running on your server, configure CometChat plugins by following the steps listed below:		\n\n*On Linux based systems :*			\n\n1. Check whether the Red5 server is up and running by visiting the URL: *http://&lt;red5 server URL or IP&gt;:5080*	\n\n2. If the Red5 server is running successfully then go to to webapps directory of your Red5 installation. If RED5 is installed using SVN then in most of the cases the webapp directory is *red5_.svn/dist/webapps.*.	\n\n3. Download the sever side package for the required plugin by executing the following command: *wget http://www.cometchat.com/extra/ccred5screenshare.tar.gz*	\n\n4. Run the given command to extract the package: *tar -xzf ccred5screenshare.tar.gz*		\n\n5. Then delete the tar file by executing the given command: *rm ccred5screenshare.tar.gz*	\n	\n6. Finally restart the Red5 server.		\n\n7.Thus you have successfully configured Red5 server with server side packages of CometChat plugins on your Linux based systems and now you can test the Screensharing plugin on your site.				\n\n*On Windows server :*\n\n1. Check whether the Red5 server is up and running by visiting the URL: *http://&lt;red5 server URL or IP&gt;:5080*\n\n2. If the Red5 server is running successfully then download the sever side package for the required plugin from *http://www.cometchat.com/extra/ccred5screenshare.zip*		\n\n3. Unzip the ccred5screenshare.zip file and move the screenshare folder to *webapps* folder of Red5 installation.		\n\n4. Finally restart the Red5 server.		\n\n5. Thus you have successfully configured Red5 server with server side packages of CometChat plugins on your Windows and now you can test the Screensharing plugin on your site.		\n\n<h4>Adobe FMS	</h4>\n		\nYou can install screenshare application on self-host adobe FMS or on third party Adobe FMS host like Influxis.	\n\n* If you would like to self-host Adobe FMS,			\n\nIf you would like to self-host Adobe FMS,	\n	\n1. Purchase, download and install Adobe FMS on your server (outside support scope).	\n		\n2. Create a folder named ‘*screenshare*’ in the applications directory of your FMS.\nFor example, if you are using FMS v4.5 on windows system then you need to create the screenshare folder in ‘*C:Program FilesAdobeFlash Media Server 4.5applications*'' folder.			\n\n3. Download *main.asc* file from the URL [http://www.cometchat.com/extra/ccfmsscreenshare.zip](http://www.cometchat.com/extra/ccfmsscreenshare.zip) and place it inside the screenshare folder.				\n\n4. Thus you have successfully installed screenshare application on your FMS.			\n\n* If you would like to use a third-party Adobe FMS host,	\n\nSign up with a host [http://www.influxis.com/](http://www.influxis.com/) and follow the steps listed below:\n\n1. Login to your Infuxis account and click on the New App Builder in the tools menu as shown in the image.			\n![main](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/08/main.png)	\n 		\n2. Type ''*screenshare*'' in the *New Application Name* field and mark *Add my own ASC file*.		\n\n3. To add your code into main.asc file, mark *Paste code into main.asc file*. You can find server side code for main.asc file at [http://www.cometchat.com/extra/ccfmsscreenshare.zip](http://www.cometchat.com/extra/ccfmsscreenshare.zip)	\n\n4. Copy the entire code from *main.asc* and paste it in *Enter your Server Side Action Script code here* area as shown in the image below.		\n![screenshare](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/08/new+application+builder.png)		\n\n5. Then click on the *Build button* to build your screenshare application		\n![screenshare](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/08/screenshare.png)		\n\n6. You can get your host address and application folder name from the prompt that appears as soon as you click on the *Build Button*.		\n![](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/08/new+capture.png)\n\nNote: In the above image,		\nYour application URL is *rtmp://xxxxx.rtmphost.com/screenshare*\nYour host address is *xxxxx.rtmphost.com*		\nAnd your application folder is *screenshare*		\nYou will have to enter the host address and application folder name in screenshare settings while configuring it through CometChat Administration Panel.		\n\nThus you have successfully installed screenshare application on the Influxis FMS.		\n\n<h4>Configuring the Plugin</h4>		\n\n* In the *CometChat Admin Panel* -&gt; Plugins section, add the *Screenshare Plugin* to your live plugins and click on the *config* link besides the name.\n\n* Enter following details:	\nHost address : *xxxxx.rtmphost.com*		\nApplication folder : *Screenshare*\n\n* Click on the *Update Settings* button and close the window.	\n	\n![Screenshare Settings](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/03/screenshare+settings.png)		\n\n#AddLive	\n\n* Point your browser to the following URL: *https://developer.addlive.com/cometchat* or click on the link in the plugin setting window to create an AddLive account if you don’t have an Application ID and an Application Auth Secret key	\n\n* Register on the site with the required details		\n\n* Once you are done with the registration process, you will receive a mail from AddLive containing the Application ID and Stable API key	\n\n* Now place these values in plugin setting window and click on the *Update* settings	\n\n![AddLive](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/03/addlive_full.png)', 'Screensharing Plugin', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2816-autosave-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:41:42', '2013-09-23 12:41:42', '', 2816, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/2816-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `ccwp_4_posts` (`ID`, `post_author`, `post_date`, `post_date_gmt`, `post_content`, `post_title`, `post_excerpt`, `post_status`, `comment_status`, `ping_status`, `post_password`, `post_name`, `to_ping`, `pinged`, `post_modified`, `post_modified_gmt`, `post_content_filtered`, `post_parent`, `guid`, `menu_order`, `post_type`, `post_mime_type`, `comment_count`) VALUES
(4678, 1, '2013-09-23 12:43:52', '2013-09-23 12:43:52', '<h4>Activating Screensharing Plugin</h4>\r\n\r\nScreensharing plugin is one of the few plugins which requires a third-party service. Screensharing can use RED5, Adobe FMS or AddLive.	\r\n\r\n<h4>Use RED5 server</h4>		\r\n\r\nIf you would like to self-host RED5 server,		\r\n\r\n* Point your browser to [http://www.red5.org/](http://www.red5.org/)		\r\n\r\n* Download and install Red5 1.0 RC1 on your server from the following link: [http://code.google.com/p/red5/](https://code.google.com/p/red5/)\r\n(outside support scope)		\r\n\r\nIf you would like to use a third-party Red5 host,		\r\n\r\n* Sign up with a host like, [http://www.red5host.com/](http://www.red5host.com/)		\r\n\r\n<h4>Installing Screensharing Plugin with RED5 server</h4>	\r\n* If you don’t have Red5 installed on your server, click the following link:		\r\n[Steps to install Red5 along with server side packages of CometChat plugins on your server](http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/tutorials/installing-red5)		\r\n\r\n* If you have Red5 up and running on your server, configure CometChat plugins by following the steps listed below:		\r\n\r\n*On Linux based systems :*			\r\n\r\n1. Check whether the Red5 server is up and running by visiting the URL: *http://&lt;red5 server URL or IP&gt;:5080*	\r\n\r\n2. If the Red5 server is running successfully then go to to webapps directory of your Red5 installation. If RED5 is installed using SVN then in most of the cases the webapp directory is *red5_.svn/dist/webapps.*.	\r\n\r\n3. Download the sever side package for the required plugin by executing the following command: *wget http://www.cometchat.com/extra/ccred5screenshare.tar.gz*	\r\n\r\n4. Run the given command to extract the package: *tar -xzf ccred5screenshare.tar.gz*		\r\n\r\n5. Then delete the tar file by executing the given command: *rm ccred5screenshare.tar.gz*	\r\n	\r\n6. Finally restart the Red5 server.		\r\n\r\n7.Thus you have successfully configured Red5 server with server side packages of CometChat plugins on your Linux based systems and now you can test the Screensharing plugin on your site.				\r\n\r\n*On Windows server :*\r\n\r\n1. Check whether the Red5 server is up and running by visiting the URL: *http://&lt;red5 server URL or IP&gt;:5080*\r\n\r\n2. If the Red5 server is running successfully then download the sever side package for the required plugin from *http://www.cometchat.com/extra/ccred5screenshare.zip*		\r\n\r\n3. Unzip the ccred5screenshare.zip file and move the screenshare folder to *webapps* folder of Red5 installation.		\r\n\r\n4. Finally restart the Red5 server.		\r\n\r\n5. Thus you have successfully configured Red5 server with server side packages of CometChat plugins on your Windows and now you can test the Screensharing plugin on your site.		\r\n\r\n<h4>Adobe FMS	</h4>\r\n		\r\nYou can install screenshare application on self-host adobe FMS or on third party Adobe FMS host like Influxis.	\r\n\r\n* If you would like to self-host Adobe FMS,			\r\n\r\nIf you would like to self-host Adobe FMS,	\r\n	\r\n1. Purchase, download and install Adobe FMS on your server (outside support scope).	\r\n		\r\n2. Create a folder named ‘*screenshare*’ in the applications directory of your FMS.\r\nFor example, if you are using FMS v4.5 on windows system then you need to create the screenshare folder in ‘*C:Program FilesAdobeFlash Media Server 4.5applications*'' folder.			\r\n\r\n3. Download *main.asc* file from the URL [http://www.cometchat.com/extra/ccfmsscreenshare.zip](http://www.cometchat.com/extra/ccfmsscreenshare.zip) and place it inside the screenshare folder.				\r\n\r\n4. Thus you have successfully installed screenshare application on your FMS.			\r\n\r\n* If you would like to use a third-party Adobe FMS host,	\r\n\r\nSign up with a host [http://www.influxis.com/](http://www.influxis.com/) and follow the steps listed below:\r\n\r\n1. Login to your Infuxis account and click on the New App Builder in the tools menu as shown in the image.			\r\n![main](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/08/main.png)	\r\n 		\r\n2. Type ''*screenshare*'' in the *New Application Name* field and mark *Add my own ASC file*.		\r\n\r\n3. To add your code into main.asc file, mark *Paste code into main.asc file*. You can find server side code for main.asc file at [http://www.cometchat.com/extra/ccfmsscreenshare.zip](http://www.cometchat.com/extra/ccfmsscreenshare.zip)	\r\n\r\n4. Copy the entire code from *main.asc* and paste it in *Enter your Server Side Action Script code here* area as shown in the image below.		\r\n![screenshare](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/08/new+application+builder.png)		\r\n\r\n5. Then click on the *Build button* to build your screenshare application		\r\n![screenshare](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/08/screenshare.png)		\r\n\r\n6. You can get your host address and application folder name from the prompt that appears as soon as you click on the *Build Button*.		\r\n![](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/08/new+capture.png)\r\n\r\nNote: In the above image,		\r\nYour application URL is *rtmp://xxxxx.rtmphost.com/screenshare*\r\nYour host address is *xxxxx.rtmphost.com*		\r\nAnd your application folder is *screenshare*		\r\nYou will have to enter the host address and application folder name in screenshare settings while configuring it through CometChat Administration Panel.		\r\n\r\nThus you have successfully installed screenshare application on the Influxis FMS.		\r\n\r\n<h4>Configuring the Plugin</h4>		\r\n\r\n* In the *CometChat Admin Panel* -&gt; Plugins section, add the *Screenshare Plugin* to your live plugins and click on the *config* link besides the name.\r\n\r\n* Enter following details:	\r\nHost address : *xxxxx.rtmphost.com*		\r\nApplication folder : *Screenshare*\r\n\r\n* Click on the *Update Settings* button and close the window.	\r\n	\r\n![Screenshare Settings](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/03/screenshare+settings.png)		\r\n\r\n<h4>AddLive</h4>\r\n\r\n* Point your browser to the following URL: *https://developer.addlive.com/cometchat* or click on the link in the plugin setting window to create an AddLive account if you don’t have an Application ID and an Application Auth Secret key	\r\n\r\n* Register on the site with the required details		\r\n\r\n* Once you are done with the registration process, you will receive a mail from AddLive containing the Application ID and Stable API key	\r\n\r\n* Now place these values in plugin setting window and click on the *Update* settings	\r\n\r\n![AddLive](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/03/addlive_full.png)', 'Screensharing Plugin', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2816-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:43:52', '2013-09-23 12:43:52', '', 2816, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/2816-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4679, 1, '2013-09-23 12:45:00', '2013-09-23 12:45:00', '<h4>Whiteboard plugin is one of the few plugins which requires a third-party service. Whiteboard can use either RED5 or Adobe FMS server.</h4>\r\n\r\n<h4>Use RED5 server</h4>\r\n\r\nIf you would like to self-host RED5 server,	\r\n	\r\n* Point your browser to [http://www.red5.org/](http://www.red5.org/)	\r\n	\r\n* Download and install **Red5 1.0 RC1** on your server from the following link: [http://code.google.com/p/red5/](http://code.google.com/p/red5/)	\r\n(outside support scope)		\r\n\r\nIf you would like to use a third-party Red5 host,	\r\n		\r\n* Sign up with a host like [http://www.red5host.com/](http://www.red5host.com/)	\r\n\r\n<h4>Installing Whiteboard Plugin with RED5 server</h4>\r\n\r\n* If you don''t have Red5 installed on your server, click the following link:	\r\n[Steps to install Red5 along with server side packages of CometChat plugins on your server](http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/tutorials/installing-red5)		\r\n\r\n* If you have Red5 up and running on your server, configure CometChat plugins by following the steps listed below:	\r\n\r\n*On Linux based systems :*\r\n\r\n1. Check whether the Red5 server is up and running by visiting the URL: *http://&lt;red5 server URL or IP&gt;:5080*	\r\n\r\n2. If the Red5 server is running successfully then go to to webapps directory of your Red5 installation. If RED5 is installed using SVN then in most of the cases the webapp directory is **red5_&lt;version&gt;.svn/dist/webapps**.\r\n\r\n3. Download the sever side package for the required plugin by executing the following command: 	\r\n**wget http://www.cometchat.com/extra/ccred5whiteboard.tar.gz**	\r\n\r\n4. Run the given command to extract the package: **tar -xzf ccred5whiteboard.tar.gz**	\r\n\r\n5. Then delete the tar file by executing the given command: **rm ccred5whiteboard.tar.gz**	\r\n\r\n6. Finally restart the Red5 server.\r\n7. Thus you have successfully configured Red5 server with server side packages of CometChat plugins on your Linux based systems and now you can test the Whiteboard plugin on your site.\r\n\r\n*On Windows server :*\r\n\r\n1. Check whether the Red5 server is up and running by visiting the URL: *http://&lt;red5 server URL or IP&gt;:5080*	\r\n\r\n2. If the Red5 server is running successfully then download the sever side package for the required plugin from *http://www.cometchat.com/extra/ccred5whiteboard.zip*	\r\n\r\n3. Unzip the ccred5whiteboard.zip file and move the whiteboard folder to **webapps** folder of Red5 installation.		\r\n\r\n4. Finally restart the Red5 server.\r\n5. Thus you have successfully configured Red5 server with server side packages of CometChat plugins on your Windows Server and now you can test the Whiteboard plugin on your site.\r\n\r\n<h4>Use Adobe FMS</h4>\r\nIf you would like to self-host Adobe FMS server,\r\n\r\n* Purchase, download and install Adobe FMS on your server (outside support scope)	\r\n	\r\nIf you would like to use a third-party Adobe FMS host,	\r\n\r\n* Sign up with a host like [http://www.influxis.com/](http://www.influxis.com/)\r\n\r\n<h4>Installing Whiteboard Plugin with FMS</h4>\r\nCreate a folder named **‘whiteboard**’ in the applications directory of your FMS.\r\n\r\nFor example, if you are using FMS v4.5 on windows system then you need to create the **whiteboard** folder in *‘C:Program FilesAdobeFlash Media Server 4.5applications‘ folder*.\r\n\r\n<h4>Configuring the Whiteboard Plugin</h4>\r\n\r\n* In the **CometChat Admin Panel**-&gt; **Plugins** section, add the **Whiteboard Plugin** to your live plugins and click on the **config** link besides the name.	\r\n\r\n* Enter the required details.	\r\n\r\n* Click on the **Update Settings** button and close the window.\r\n\r\n![whiteboard plugin]\r\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/06/whiteboard+settings1-e1339765516552.png)', 'Whiteboard Plugin', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2600-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:45:00', '2013-09-23 12:45:00', '', 2600, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/2600-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4680, 1, '2013-09-23 12:47:36', '2013-09-23 12:47:36', '<h4>Using your own Facebook Application</h4>\n\nIf your site already uses Facebook to allow users to login, then you can use the same Facebook Application when your users connect via CometChat to chat with their Facebook friends.\n\n<h4>Configuring your Facebook Application</h4>		\n\n* Login to Facebook and go to your application in the developers section		\n\n* Note the *App ID* and *App Secret*		\n\n![Facebook app](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/03/facebook+app.png)		\n\n* Click on *Edit Settings* and update your *App Domain* to include *chatforyoursite.com*		\n\n* Then update *Mobile Web URL* to *http://chatforyoursite.com*		\n\n**Do not rename “chatforyoursite.com” to “chatforYOURACTUALSITENAME.com”. It is meant to be “chatforyoursite.com”, a domain that we own and use to enable Facebook chat**.	\n	\n![facebook+app+1](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/03/facebook+app+1.png)		\n\n* Click on the *Save Changes* button and wait 3-10 minutes for the changes to propagate.		\n\n<h4>Configuring the extension</h4>	\n\n1. In the Extensions section, add the *Facebook/Gtalk/XMPP extension* to your *live extensions* and click on the *config* link besides the name.		\n		\n2. Enter the details you noted previously			\n\n3. Click on the *Update Settings* button and close the window\n\n![Facebook configuration](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/03/facebook+config.png)\n\n<blockquote>\n<p>If you do not want the user to see the Facebook permissions dialog when logging into chat, add the following parameters in your Facebook Connect settings: offline_access, xmpp_login</p>\n</blockquote>			\n	\n\n<h4>Using your own Gtalk Application</h4>\nSimilar to facebook appplication, if your site already uses google to allow users to login, then you can use the same google Application when your users connect via CometChat to chat with their Gtalk friends.	\n\n<h4>Configuring your Gtalk Application</h4>\n\n* Login to Google and go to your application in the developers section ( for this point your browser to the following: *https://code.google.com/apis/console/*)		\n\n* Note the *Client ID* and *Client Secret*\n\n![Gtalk configuration](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/03/screenshot1.png)	\n\n* Click on Edit Settings and update your App Domain to include *chatforyoursite.com*		\n		\n* Set Authorized Redirect URL to: 	\n*http://j.chatforyoursite.com/gtalk.html*	\n*https://j.chatforyoursite.com/gtalk.html*	\n	\n* Then Set Authorized Javascript Origins to:	\n*http://j.chatforyoursite.com*  	\n*https://j.chatforyoursite.com*\n\n![Google Settings](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/03/google_editsettings.png)		\n\n* Click on the Save Changes button and wait 3-10 minutes for the changes to propagate.		\n\n<h4>Configuring the extension</h4>	\n\n1. In the Extensions section, add the *Facebook/Gtalk/XMPP extension* to your *live extensions* and click on the *config* link besides the name.	\n		\n2. Enter the details you noted previously			\n\n3. Click on the *Update Settings* button and close the window\n\n![Settings](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/03/fbgtalk+settings+-+Copy.png)', 'Facebook/Gtalk/XMPP Extension', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '634-autosave-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:47:36', '2013-09-23 12:47:36', '', 634, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/634-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4681, 1, '2013-09-23 12:47:38', '2013-09-23 12:47:38', '<h4>Using your own Facebook Application</h4>\r\n\r\nIf your site already uses Facebook to allow users to login, then you can use the same Facebook Application when your users connect via CometChat to chat with their Facebook friends.\r\n\r\n<h4>Configuring your Facebook Application</h4>		\r\n\r\n* Login to Facebook and go to your application in the developers section		\r\n\r\n* Note the *App ID* and *App Secret*		\r\n\r\n![Facebook app](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/03/facebook+app.png)		\r\n\r\n* Click on *Edit Settings* and update your *App Domain* to include *chatforyoursite.com*		\r\n\r\n* Then update *Mobile Web URL* to *http://chatforyoursite.com*		\r\n\r\n**Do not rename “chatforyoursite.com” to “chatforYOURACTUALSITENAME.com”. It is meant to be “chatforyoursite.com”, a domain that we own and use to enable Facebook chat**.	\r\n	\r\n![facebook+app+1](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/03/facebook+app+1.png)		\r\n\r\n* Click on the *Save Changes* button and wait 3-10 minutes for the changes to propagate.		\r\n\r\n<h4>Configuring the extension</h4>	\r\n\r\n1. In the Extensions section, add the *Facebook/Gtalk/XMPP extension* to your *live extensions* and click on the *config* link besides the name.		\r\n		\r\n2. Enter the details you noted previously			\r\n\r\n3. Click on the *Update Settings* button and close the window\r\n\r\n![Facebook configuration](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/03/facebook+config.png)\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>If you do not want the user to see the Facebook permissions dialog when logging into chat, add the following parameters in your Facebook Connect settings: offline_access, xmpp_login</p>\r\n</blockquote>			\r\n	\r\n\r\n<h4>Using your own Gtalk Application</h4>\r\nSimilar to facebook appplication, if your site already uses google to allow users to login, then you can use the same google Application when your users connect via CometChat to chat with their Gtalk friends.	\r\n\r\n<h4>Configuring your Gtalk Application</h4>\r\n\r\n* Login to Google and go to your application in the developers section ( for this point your browser to the following: *https://code.google.com/apis/console/*)		\r\n\r\n* Note the *Client ID* and *Client Secret*\r\n\r\n![Gtalk configuration](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/03/screenshot1.png)	\r\n\r\n* Click on Edit Settings and update your App Domain to include *chatforyoursite.com*		\r\n		\r\n* Set Authorized Redirect URL to: 	\r\n*http://j.chatforyoursite.com/gtalk.html*	\r\n*https://j.chatforyoursite.com/gtalk.html*	\r\n	\r\n* Then Set Authorized Javascript Origins to:	\r\n*http://j.chatforyoursite.com*  	\r\n*https://j.chatforyoursite.com*\r\n\r\n![Google Settings](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/03/google_editsettings.png)		\r\n\r\n* Click on the Save Changes button and wait 3-10 minutes for the changes to propagate.		\r\n\r\n<h4>Configuring the extension</h4>	\r\n\r\n1. In the Extensions section, add the *Facebook/Gtalk/XMPP extension* to your *live extensions* and click on the *config* link besides the name.	\r\n		\r\n2. Enter the details you noted previously			\r\n\r\n3. Click on the *Update Settings* button and close the window\r\n\r\n![Settings](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/03/fbgtalk+settings+-+Copy.png)', 'Facebook/Gtalk/XMPP Extension', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '634-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:47:38', '2013-09-23 12:47:38', '', 634, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/634-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4682, 1, '2013-09-23 12:47:54', '2013-09-23 12:47:54', 'You can add *custom advertisements* to chat boxes and earn money when your users chat. Advertisements will be automatically displayed in the active chat box.\r\nYou can use any *custom HTML code* as per your requirements.	\r\n\r\n<h4>Configuring the Module</h4>\r\n\r\n1. In the *Extensions* section, add the *Advertisement extension* to your live extensions and click on the *Configure Module* icon besides the name.	\r\n\r\n2. Enter your *Advertisement HTML code* and set the *Ad height*.	\r\n\r\n3. Click on the *Update Settings* button and close the window.		\r\n\r\n![Advertisement Settings](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/05/Advertisement+Settings.png)', 'Advertisements', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1569-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:47:54', '2013-09-23 12:47:54', '', 1569, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/1569-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4683, 1, '2013-09-23 12:48:11', '2013-09-23 12:48:11', 'With this feature your site users will get the latest notifications of all the newly arrived messages, on clicking these alerts he or she will get access to CometChat mobile web app where they can view all the messages.\r\n\r\n<h4>Configuring the extension	</h4>\r\n\r\n1. In the Extensions section, add the *Mobile Tab extension* to your *live extensions* and click on the *config* link besides the name.	\r\n\r\n2. Enter the size of mobiletab in percentile (100% corresponds to default size of the mobiletab)	\r\n\r\n3. Click on the *Update Settings* button and close the window.	\r\n\r\n![Mobile Tab](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/03/mobiletab.png)', 'Mobile Tab', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '4164-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:48:11', '2013-09-23 12:48:11', '', 4164, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/4164-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4684, 1, '2013-09-23 12:48:50', '2013-09-23 12:48:50', '<h4>Setting Up</h4>\r\n\r\n1. Decide which theme you would like to use as base. \r\n2. Select the *clone* option next to the theme you would like to use as base.\r\n3. Type a new name for the theme and click on the *Add Theme* button.\r\n\r\n![Create New Theme]\r\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/05/Create+New+Theme+.png)\r\n\r\n<h4>Using Theme Editor</h4>\r\n1. Click on *Edit Theme* link next to the theme you want to edit.\r\n2. If you want to modify the base colors, you can do so by quickly using our inbuilt *Theme Color Editor*.\r\n3. If you want to modify a specific style, you can manually edit the CSS files.\r\n\r\n![Theme Editor]\r\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/05/Theme+Editor.png)\r\n\r\n<h4>How to know which style to edit?</h4>\r\n1. Install Firebug for Firefox.\r\n2. Using the Inspect function select the portion you want to find out the class/ID name.\r\n3. Add the relevant code to the CSS file.', 'Creating New Theme', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '197-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:48:50', '2013-09-23 12:48:50', '', 197, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/197-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4685, 1, '2013-09-23 12:49:31', '2013-09-23 12:49:31', 'CometChat offers *8 additional languages* with which you can manage the language of the CometChat bar and plugins. You also have the option to add new languages to the existing list.\r\n\r\nLanguages that CometChat offers includes\r\n\r\n1. Chinese\r\n2. Portuguese\r\n3. Japanese\r\n4. Italian\r\n5. French\r\n6. Spanish\r\n7. German\r\n8. Arabic\r\n\r\n<h4>Preview a language</h4>\r\n\r\nWith this option, you can have a view of all the sections of CometChat in the language of your choice.\r\n\r\nFor example, click on the *Preview Language* button next to French to get a view of all the sections of CometChat that has been translated to *French*.\r\n \r\n![Language preview]\r\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/05/Language+preview.png)\r\n\r\n<h4>Add Language</h4>\r\n\r\nTo import a language to the existing list of languages, click on the *Add Language* button.', 'Additional languages', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1899-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:49:31', '2013-09-23 12:49:31', '', 1899, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/1899-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4686, 1, '2013-09-23 12:50:12', '2013-09-23 12:50:12', 'With this feature, you can view the *chat logs* of the users of your site.\r\n\r\nTo view the chat logs, you need to go to *CometChat Admin Panel -&gt; Logs*	\r\n\r\n![Logs](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/03/log.png)	\r\n\r\n<h4>One-on-one Chat</h4>\r\n\r\n* Click on ''*One-on-one Chat*'' and enter the User ID or Username	\r\n\r\n* Click on the *Search Logs* button, for example, let the Username be Melissa		\r\n\r\n![Search Logs](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/05/search+logs.png)	\r\n\r\n* Then Click on the *username* i.e. ‘Melissa‘.\r\n\r\n![Logs](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/05/logs.png)		\r\n\r\n* Select the user between whom you want to view the conversation, for example, select ‘John’ if you want to view the conversation between Melissa and John		\r\n\r\n![Logs](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/05/logs+2.png)		\r\n\r\n* Now you can have a view at the complete *chat log* and also have a view at Melissa’s other conversation by clicking on the click here link.\r\n\r\n![Logs](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/05/log+3.png)		\r\n\r\n<h4>Chatroom</h4>\r\n\r\nTo view the chat log of a chatroom, follow the steps listed below:\r\n\r\n* Click on the ''*chatrooms*'' option		\r\n\r\n![Chatrooms](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/03/chatrooms1-Copy.png)		\r\n\r\n* As you select the chatroom option, a list of *active chatrooms* appears	\r\n\r\n* Select the required chatroom, for example select ''*Fun Zone*'' chatroom\r\n\r\n![Chatrooms](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/03/chatrooms1.png)	\r\n\r\n* Once you select Fun Zone, you will be able to view the entire chat log\r\n\r\n![Chatroom logs](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/03/funzone-logs.png)', 'Logs', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1966-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:50:12', '2013-09-23 12:50:12', '', 1966, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/1966-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4687, 1, '2013-09-23 12:51:11', '2013-09-23 12:51:11', 'CometService offloads 95% of work to our servers and reduces message delivery time.	\r\n\r\nCometService can be activated directly from the CometChat Administration Panel. \r\n\r\nTo use CometService, you need to perform two easy steps.\r\n\r\n<h4>Obtaining Keys</h4>\r\n\r\n1. Point your browser to [http://www.cometchat.com/cometservice](http://www.cometchat.com/cometservice) and select a plan of your choice\r\n2. After subscribing, you will receive an automated email from us\r\n3. Login to CometChat.com and visit [http://www.cometchat.com/my/cometservice](http://www.cometchat.com/my/cometservice)\r\n4. Copy the keys from the page \r\n\r\n<h4>Adding the Keys</h4>\r\n1. Login to *CometChat Administration Panel*\r\n2. Select *Settings -&gt; CometService*\r\n3. Enter the keys and set *Use CometService* to *Yes*\r\n\r\n![Comet Service]\r\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/04/CometService.png)\r\n\r\n', 'CometService', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1383-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:51:11', '2013-09-23 12:51:11', '', 1383, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/1383-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4688, 1, '2013-09-23 12:51:27', '2013-09-23 12:51:27', 'With this feature, you can enable your visitors to automatically log into CometChat when they visit your site as Guests12432 etc.\r\n\r\nYou can configure which set of users will be displayed in the Who’s Online List for logged in users as well as for visitors.		\r\n\r\n<h4>Guest Chat Configuration</h4>		\r\n1. Login to *CometChat Administration Panel*	\r\n\r\n2. Select *Settings -&gt; Guest Chat*	\r\n\r\n3. Enable *Guest Chat*	\r\n\r\n4. Set the *Prefix for guest names, Who’s Online List for guests* and *logged in users* accordingly.	\r\n\r\n5. Click on the *Update* button		\r\n\r\n![Guest Chat](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/03/guestchat.png)', 'Guest Chat', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1409-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:51:27', '2013-09-23 12:51:27', '', 1409, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/1409-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4689, 1, '2013-09-23 12:52:23', '2013-09-23 12:52:23', '<h4> Quick steps</h4>\r\n\r\n1. Disable chat history plugin and do not use logs option in admin panel\r\n2. Run http://www.yoursite.com/cometchat/cron.php periodically (every 3 hours)\r\n3. Show CometChat only for logged in users (i.e. hide bar for non-logged in users)\r\n4. Set CometChat to show only online friends/users in *Who''s Online* list\r\n5. Move the CometChat HTML code from just after `` to just before ``\r\n6. If you are using standalone integration, make sure that your mySQL queries are optimized\r\n\r\n<h4>Alternatives</h4>\r\n\r\nIf your server is unable to handle the load, we suggest you subscribe to our [CometService](http://www.cometchat.com/cometservice). We also provide alternative transports- Self-hosted APE server, PusherApp and BeaconPush which can be used instead of CometService.', 'Optimizing Performance', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '86-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:52:23', '2013-09-23 12:52:23', '', 86, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/86-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4690, 1, '2013-09-23 12:53:02', '2013-09-23 12:53:02', '<h4>Login to Administration Panel</h4>\r\n\r\n1. Point your browser to your CometChat Admin Panel\r\n2. Login and visit the settings page\r\n\r\n<h4>Resizing the CometChat bar</h4>\r\n\r\nThe *Bar layout* can be set to the following:\r\n\r\n1. *Fluid* - The bar will be resized dynamically as the browser window is resized\r\n2. *Fixed* - The bar width will remain fixed irrespective of the size of the browser window\r\n\r\nWe highly recommend that you do not set the *width of the bar in pixels* is set to *960* or higher in case of *Fixed* bar layout.\r\n\r\n<h4>Positioning the CometChat bar</h4>\r\n\r\nThe bar can be docked either on the left, center or right horizontally. Vertically, the position is always fixed to the bottom of the browser window.\r\n\r\nThe bar can be aligned only when the *Bar layout* is fixed. Edit the drop down *If set to fixed, enter alignment of the bar* as per your requirements.\r\n\r\n*Padding of bar* allows you to add spacing between the bar and the ends of the horizontal ends of the browser window.', 'Positioning and resizing the bar', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '80-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:53:02', '2013-09-23 12:53:02', '', 80, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/80-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4691, 1, '2013-09-23 12:53:35', '2013-09-23 12:53:35', '<h4>Login to Administration Panel</h4>\r\n\r\n1. Point your browser to your CometChat Admin Panel\r\n2. Login and visit the settings page\r\n\r\n<h4>Activation</h4>\r\n\r\nThe lite version of CometChat can be activated by setting the *Switch on light-weight chat?* to *Yes* and clicking on the *Update Settings* button at the bottom of the page.\r\n\r\n<h4>Advantages</h4>\r\n\r\n1. Light weight means faster loading times\r\n2. Facebook-like chat\r\n3. Unobtrusive and minimalistic\r\n\r\n<h4>Disadvantages</h4>\r\n\r\n1. Does not allow use of *Modules* directly on the bar (they can be embedded in your page)\r\n2. Multiple chat boxes not fitting within the browser window will not add scroll arrows', 'Using Lite Version', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '83-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:53:35', '2013-09-23 12:53:35', '', 83, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/83-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4692, 1, '2013-09-23 12:53:58', '2013-09-23 12:53:58', 'This guide will assist you to match the CometChat default theme with your site colors. This is basic tutorial can help you theme CometChat even if you have no knowledge about CSS.\r\n\r\nYou can always use our in-built theme editor to change colors directly via ***CometChat Administration Panel***.\r\n\r\nYou can edit your theme with the help of  two simple tools.\r\n\r\n<h4>Color Changer</h4>\r\nYou can change the base color with the help of slider.\r\n\r\n![Color Changer]\r\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/05/Color+changer.png)\r\n\r\n<h4>Theme Variables</h4>\r\n\r\nWith Theme Variables you can edit or set colors, font family and font sizes of your theme.\r\n\r\n![Theme variables]\r\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/05/Theme+variable.png)\r\n\r\nFor example, to set the background color of your bar, click on the ***color box*** that is next to bar_background and then select the desired color accordingly.	\r\nSimilarly you can change the other theme variables as well.\r\n\r\n![Bar background]\r\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/05/bar+background.png)\r\n\r\nAfter the modification, CometChat will look like:	\r\n\r\n![Theming]\r\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2012/05/Theming.png)', 'Theming CometChat to match your site colors', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '486-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:53:58', '2013-09-23 12:53:58', '', 486, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/486-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4693, 1, '2013-09-23 12:54:55', '2013-09-23 12:54:55', 'CometService offloads 95% of work to our servers and reduces message delivery time.\r\n\r\nCometService can be activated directly from the CometChat Administration Panel.\r\n\r\nTo use CometService, you need to perform two easy steps.		\r\n\r\n<h4>Obtaining Keys</h4>		\r\n		\r\n1. Point your browser to [http://www.cometchat.com/cometservice](http://www.cometchat.com/cometservice) and select a plan of your choice.	\r\n\r\n2. After subscribing, you will receive an automated email from us.	\r\n\r\n3. Login to CometChat.com and visit [http://www.cometchat.com/my/cometservice](http://www.cometchat.com/my/cometservice)	\r\n\r\n4. Copy the keys from the page.		\r\n\r\n<h4>Adding the Keys</h4>	\r\n\r\n1. Login to *CometChat Administration Panel*		\r\n\r\n2. Select *Settings* -&gt; *CometService*		\r\n\r\n3. Enter the keys and set *Use CometService* to *Yes*	\r\n\r\n![CometService](http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/03/cometservice.png)', 'Using CometService', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '105-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:54:55', '2013-09-23 12:54:55', '', 105, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/105-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4694, 1, '2013-09-23 12:55:21', '2013-09-23 12:55:21', '&gt; You need to purchase the APE server transport before proceeding with the steps below. To purchase, please create a support ticket.\r\n\r\n<h4>Installation of APE Server</h4>\r\n\r\n1. Visit [http://www.ape-project.org](http://www.ape-project.org) and [download APE Server](http://www.ape-project.org/download/)\r\n2. [Install APE Server](http://www.ape-project.org/wiki/index.php/Setup) on any standard VPS or dedicated server\r\n\r\n&gt; We do not provide support for installation and/or maintenance of APE Server. Please use any third-party service to manage your APE server installation. We recommend APE Server only for users who wish to handle all their communication internally. For cheaper alternatives of CometService, we suggest you use BeaconPush or PusherApp.\r\n\r\n<h4>Configuring CometChat</h4>\r\n\r\n1. Upload the *ape* folder to the *cometchat/transports* folder\r\n2. Edit *cometchat/transports/ape/config.php*\r\n3. Edit *cometchat/config.php* and find *COMET*.\r\n\r\nModify the code to the following:\r\n\r\n    define(''USE_COMET'',''1'');\r\n    define(''COMET_HISTORY_LIMIT'',''100'');\r\n    define(''KEY_A'',''RANDOMSTRING1'');\r\n    define(''KEY_B'',''RANDOMSTRING2'');\r\n    define(''KEY_C'',''RANDOMSTRING3'');\r\n    define(''SAVE_LOGS'',''0'');\r\n	\r\n    /* COMET END */\r\n	\r\n    define(''TRANSPORT'',''ape'');', 'Using APE Server', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '112-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:55:21', '2013-09-23 12:55:21', '', 112, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/112-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4695, 1, '2013-09-23 12:55:45', '2013-09-23 12:55:45', '&gt; You need to purchase the BeaconPush transport before proceeding with the steps below. To purchase, please create a support ticket.\r\n\r\n<h4>Obtaining the keys</h4>\r\n\r\nVisit [http://www.beaconpush.com](http://www.beaconpush.com) and register on the site. Note the relevant keys.\r\n\r\n<h4>Adding the keys</h4>\r\n\r\n1. Upload the *beaconpush* folder to the *cometchat/transports* folder\r\n2. Edit *cometchat/transports/beaconpush/config.php*\r\n3. Edit *cometchat/config.php* and find *COMET*.\r\n\r\nModify the code to the following:\r\n\r\n	define(''USE_COMET'',''1'');\r\n	define(''COMET_HISTORY_LIMIT'',''100'');\r\n	define(''KEY_A'',''RANDOMSTRING1'');\r\n	define(''KEY_B'',''RANDOMSTRING2'');\r\n	define(''KEY_C'',''RANDOMSTRING3'');\r\n	define(''SAVE_LOGS'',''0'');\r\n	\r\n	/* COMET END */\r\n	\r\n	define(''TRANSPORT'',''beaconpush'');', 'Using BeaconPush', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '110-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:55:45', '2013-09-23 12:55:45', '', 110, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/110-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4696, 1, '2013-09-23 12:56:07', '2013-09-23 12:56:07', '&gt; You need to purchase the Pusher transport before proceeding with the steps below. To purchase, please create a support ticket.\r\n\r\n<h4> Obtaining the keys</h4>\r\n\r\nVisit [http://www.pusher.com](http://www.pusher.com) and register on the site. Create a new app and get the relevant keys.\r\n\r\n<h4> Adding the keys</h4>\r\n\r\n1. Upload the *pusher* folder to the *cometchat/transports* folder\r\n2. Edit *cometchat/transports/pusher/config.php*\r\n3. Edit *cometchat/config.php* and find *COMET*.\r\n\r\nModify the code to the following:\r\n\r\n	define(''USE_COMET'',''1'');\r\n	define(''COMET_HISTORY_LIMIT'',''100'');\r\n	define(''KEY_A'',''RANDOMSTRING1'');\r\n	define(''KEY_B'',''RANDOMSTRING2'');\r\n	define(''KEY_C'',''RANDOMSTRING3'');\r\n	define(''SAVE_LOGS'',''0'');\r\n	\r\n	/* COMET END */\r\n	\r\n	define(''TRANSPORT'',''pusher'');', 'Using PusherApp', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '107-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:56:07', '2013-09-23 12:56:07', '', 107, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/107-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4697, 1, '2013-09-23 12:56:55', '2013-09-23 12:56:55', 'chatWith() function assists you to dynamically launch a chat box directly from your web paget.\r\n\r\n<h4>The API</h4>\r\n\r\nThe chatWith() function is used to launch a chat box. The input parameter is the user''s ID with whom the conversation has to be initiated.\r\n\r\n	jqcc.cometchat.chatWith(''USERID'');\r\n\r\n<h4>Sample Code</h4>\r\n\r\nThe ideal use of this function is in profile pages i.e. to add a "Chat with me" link to profiles.\r\n\r\n	<a href="void(0)">Chat with me</a>', 'chatWith()', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '273-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:56:55', '2013-09-23 12:56:55', '', 273, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/273-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4698, 1, '2013-09-23 13:03:02', '2013-09-23 13:03:02', 'CometChat can be downloaded directly from our website. Simply click on *My Purchases* link and download the latest version.\r\n\r\n<img src="<?php echo BASE_URL . "public/img/download_cometchat.png"; ?>" alt="instant-notification image"/>\r\n\r\nIf you plan to install CometChat on a test domain initially, make sure you enter the same domain before download. You can change the domain later, when you move to your production site.\r\n\r\nIf you are planning to use CometChat for a custom coded site, then select the *Standalone Site* integration from the drop-down menu. \r\n\r\n&gt; By default, the latest version of CometChat is already selected. We recommend you download the latest unless you have a strong reason not to do so.\r\n\r\n<img src="<?php echo BASE_URL . "public/img/download_cometchat.png"; ?>" alt="instant-notification image"/>', 'Downloading CometChat', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '168-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 13:03:02', '2013-09-23 13:03:02', '', 168, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/168-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4699, 1, '2013-09-23 13:04:35', '2013-09-23 13:04:35', '', 'downloading-cometchat', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'downloading_cometchat', '', '', '2013-09-23 13:04:35', '2013-09-23 13:04:35', '', 168, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/09/downloading_cometchat.png', 0, 'attachment', 'image/png', 0),
(4700, 1, '2013-09-23 13:06:47', '2013-09-23 13:06:47', '<p>CometChat can be downloaded directly from our website. Simply click on *My Purchases* link and download the latest version.</p><p><a href="http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/09/downloading_cometchat.png" data-mce-href="http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/09/downloading_cometchat.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-4699" alt="downloading-cometchat" src="http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/09/downloading_cometchat-300x192.png" width="300" height="192" data-mce-src="http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/09/downloading_cometchat-300x192.png"></a></p><p>If you plan to install CometChat on a test domain initially, make sure you enter the same domain before download. You can change the domain later, when you move to your production site.</p><p>If you are planning to use CometChat for a custom coded site, then select the *Standalone Site* integration from the drop-down menu.</p><p>&gt; By default, the latest version of CometChat is already selected. We recommend you download the latest unless you have a strong reason not to do so.</p><p><img alt="" src="&lt;?php echo BASE_URL . " data-mce-src="&lt;?php echo BASE_URL . ">" alt="instant-notification image"/&gt;</p>', 'Downloading CometChat', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '168-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 13:06:47', '2013-09-23 13:06:47', '', 168, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/168-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4701, 1, '2013-09-23 13:08:30', '2013-09-23 13:08:30', 'CometChat can be downloaded directly from our website. Simply click on *My Purchases* link and download the latest version.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/09/downloading_cometchat.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-4699" alt="downloading-cometchat" src="http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/09/downloading_cometchat-300x192.png" width="300" height="192" /></a>\r\n\r\nIf you plan to install CometChat on a test domain initially, make sure you enter the same domain before download. You can change the domain later, when you move to your production site.\r\n\r\nIf you are planning to use CometChat for a custom coded site, then select the *Standalone Site* integration from the drop-down menu.\r\n\r\n&gt; By default, the latest version of CometChat is already selected. We recommend you download the latest unless you have a strong reason not to do so.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/09/downloading_cometchat.png"><img src="http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/09/downloading_cometchat-300x192.png" alt="downloading-cometchat" width="300" height="192" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-4699" /></a>', 'Downloading CometChat', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '168-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 13:08:30', '2013-09-23 13:08:30', '', 168, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/168-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4702, 1, '2013-09-23 13:09:38', '2013-09-23 13:09:38', 'CometChat can be downloaded directly from our website. Simply click on *My Purchases* link and download the latest version.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/09/downloading_cometchat.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-4699" alt="downloading-cometchat" src="http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/09/downloading_cometchat-300x192.png" width="300" height="192" /></a>\r\n\r\nIf you plan to install CometChat on a test domain initially, make sure you enter the same domain before download. You can change the domain later, when you move to your production site.\r\n\r\nIf you are planning to use CometChat for a custom coded site, then select the *Standalone Site* integration from the drop-down menu.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<blockquote>&gt; By default, the latest version of CometChat is already selected. We recommend you download the latest unless you have a strong reason not to do so.</blockquote>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<a href="http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/09/downloading_cometchat.png"><img src="http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/09/downloading_cometchat-300x192.png" alt="downloading-cometchat" width="300" height="192" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-4699" /></a>', 'Downloading CometChat', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '168-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 13:09:38', '2013-09-23 13:09:38', '', 168, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/168-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4703, 1, '2013-09-23 13:09:56', '2013-09-23 13:09:56', 'CometChat can be downloaded directly from our website. Simply click on *My Purchases* link and download the latest version.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/09/downloading_cometchat.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-4699" alt="downloading-cometchat" src="http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/09/downloading_cometchat-300x192.png" width="300" height="192" /></a>\r\n\r\nIf you plan to install CometChat on a test domain initially, make sure you enter the same domain before download. You can change the domain later, when you move to your production site.\r\n\r\nIf you are planning to use CometChat for a custom coded site, then select the *Standalone Site* integration from the drop-down menu.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<blockquote>By default, the latest version of CometChat is already selected. We recommend you download the latest unless you have a strong reason not to do so.</blockquote>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<a href="http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/09/downloading_cometchat.png"><img src="http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/09/downloading_cometchat-300x192.png" alt="downloading-cometchat" width="300" height="192" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-4699" /></a>', 'Downloading CometChat', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '168-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 13:09:56', '2013-09-23 13:09:56', '', 168, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/168-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(4704, 1, '2013-09-23 13:12:04', '2013-09-23 13:12:04', 'CometChat can be downloaded directly from our website. Simply click on *My Purchases* link and download the latest version.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/09/downloading_cometchat.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-4699" alt="downloading-cometchat" src="http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/09/downloading_cometchat-300x192.png" width="300" height="192" /></a>\r\n\r\nIf you plan to install CometChat on a test domain initially, make sure you enter the same domain before download. You can change the domain later, when you move to your production site.\r\n\r\nIf you are planning to use CometChat for a custom coded site, then select the *Standalone Site* integration from the drop-down menu.\r\n\r\n<blockquote>By default, the latest version of CometChat is already selected. We recommend you download the latest unless you have a strong reason not to do so.&gt;</blockquote>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<a href="http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/09/downloading_cometchat.png"><img src="http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2013/09/downloading_cometchat-300x192.png" alt="downloading-cometchat" width="300" height="192" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-4699" /></a>', 'Downloading CometChat', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '168-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-23 13:12:04', '2013-09-23 13:12:04', '', 168, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/documentation/2013/09/23/168-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
